WEBVTT

00:19.219 --> 00:22.221
[rock music]

00:34.734 --> 00:36.902
<i>(male #1)</i>
<i>Americans love to race.</i>

00:39.706 --> 00:42.174
Seems once we make something go

00:42.176 --> 00:45.144
<i>you wanna make it go faster.</i>

00:45.146 --> 00:47.513
<i>And once it goes faster</i>

00:47.515 --> 00:51.683
<i>well, let's see</i>
<i>who can make it go the fastest.</i>

00:51.685 --> 00:54.486
<i>In drag racing,</i>
<i>it's all about acceleration.</i>

00:54.488 --> 00:57.222
<i>In drift,</i>
<i>it's all about style points.</i>

00:57.224 --> 01:00.726
<i>In NASCAR, well,</i>
<i>it's a lotta left turns.</i>

01:03.396 --> 01:05.397
<i>But in our world..</i>

01:10.603 --> 01:12.805
<i>...it's all about dirt.</i>

01:13.907 --> 01:15.908
[engine revving]

01:19.612 --> 01:23.282
(Seaver)
'We're in Round 1 of Lucas Oil
Off Road Racing Series.'

01:23.284 --> 01:26.618
'Trent Lerion's troubles
continue heading to lap 10.'

01:28.588 --> 01:30.222
He's gettin' squeezed out there.

01:30.224 --> 01:32.124
You're gettin' squeezed
out there, man.

01:32.126 --> 01:34.159
Tell me something I don't know.
I'm covered in sludge out here.

01:36.696 --> 01:38.764
He's running out of mud shields.

01:38.766 --> 01:41.967
Well, he wouldn't be so dirty
if he ever had the lead.

01:41.969 --> 01:43.635
(Seaver)
'Behind the leaders,
Trent Lerion

01:43.637 --> 01:45.304
'is making his move
on Greg Adler.'

01:45.306 --> 01:48.774
'Battlin' it out for the last
spot on the podium.'

01:48.776 --> 01:50.375
He's gotta make
a move on Turn 2.

01:50.377 --> 01:52.911
- Trent, you gotta--
- Yeah, I got this.

01:52.913 --> 01:55.881
(Seaver)
'Lerion's Number 7 Rockstar car
is all over Adler.'

01:55.883 --> 01:58.550
'Now, he goes to make a move,
but Adler shuts him down again''

01:58.552 --> 02:00.119
'That has to frustrate Lerion.'

02:00.121 --> 02:02.054
'He just can't find
an opening out there.'

02:03.823 --> 02:05.324
He's too close.

02:05.326 --> 02:07.292
(Seaver)
'No! Oh, no!'

02:07.294 --> 02:10.162
'He lands on Adler's bumper,
slams into the K-rail.'

02:10.164 --> 02:11.630
(Arnold)
'That's gonna do some damage.'

02:11.632 --> 02:13.132
[sighs]
Tell me somethin'.

02:13.134 --> 02:14.333
Status, brother.

02:14.335 --> 02:16.502
Uh, engine's sputtering.

02:16.504 --> 02:19.138
Tire's flat and I'm pretty sure
the rear dip is broke.

02:19.140 --> 02:20.339
Dip's gone.

02:21.841 --> 02:23.308
That's it, we're done.

02:24.811 --> 02:26.178
Damn it!

02:26.180 --> 02:27.579
(Seaver)
'Well, that looks like'

02:27.581 --> 02:29.414
'the end of the day
for Trent Lerion'

02:29.416 --> 02:31.550
'and his Number 7
Rockstar team.'

02:36.122 --> 02:38.190
[dramatic music]

02:38.192 --> 02:40.192
[sirens blaring]

02:41.761 --> 02:43.629
- Suspect in sight.
- 'Heads up, Dez.'

02:43.631 --> 02:46.298
(female #1)
'More po-po coming
from Alameda.'

02:46.300 --> 02:48.033
Alright, flip around,
300 yards on your left.

02:48.035 --> 02:50.035
The alley will give you
some breathing room.

02:50.037 --> 02:51.770
[tires screeching]

02:59.879 --> 03:02.381
- Damn it, I can't see a thing.
- Quick right.

03:11.457 --> 03:13.692
Anymore five-O?

03:13.694 --> 03:16.295
Looking. Nothing.

03:18.965 --> 03:20.532
'Nothing.'

03:22.535 --> 03:25.837
Go left on Viaduct Street.
Then it's open for a bit.

03:25.839 --> 03:27.172
No, I'm good.

03:27.174 --> 03:28.674
♪ Can't touch this

03:28.676 --> 03:30.876
- I'mma coast right in.
- No. Viaduct is safer.

03:30.878 --> 03:33.979
- You need to listen to me.
- 'Ha. They off me.'

03:33.981 --> 03:36.081
Alright, don't worry about it.
We good, man.

03:36.083 --> 03:38.417
[sighs]

03:38.419 --> 03:39.585
♪ Can't touch this

03:39.587 --> 03:41.753
♪ My music hits me so hard

03:41.755 --> 03:43.222
♪ Makes me say oh my Lord

03:43.224 --> 03:45.090
♪ Thank you for blessin' me

03:45.092 --> 03:46.658
♪ With a mind to rhyme
and two hype feet ♪

03:46.660 --> 03:48.160
♪ It feels good

03:48.162 --> 03:49.595
(woman on radio)
'Unit 17, suspect spotted.'

03:49.597 --> 03:52.331
'Headed east bound on Bronson.'

03:52.333 --> 03:53.999
Oh, shit, Dez,
crews are closin' in fast!

03:54.001 --> 03:55.667
Yo, get outta there!

03:55.669 --> 03:57.736
I got him.

03:57.738 --> 03:58.904
Where to?

04:01.574 --> 04:02.841
Down Ellis Street.

04:05.945 --> 04:08.714
Suspect in sight,
headed east on Bronson.

04:08.716 --> 04:11.283
Mother Teresa, Mary,
Moses, Paul, John.

04:11.285 --> 04:13.252
Where you going, man?

04:13.254 --> 04:15.754
[siren blaring]

04:20.893 --> 04:21.960
Oh, shit!

04:26.766 --> 04:28.200
Oh!

04:28.202 --> 04:31.036
[siren blaring]

04:31.038 --> 04:33.005
[breathing heavily]

04:54.494 --> 04:56.495
[all laughing]

04:59.599 --> 05:01.233
- Play it again?
- No more.

05:01.235 --> 05:04.102
Everybody, back to work.

05:04.104 --> 05:05.904
Come on.

05:05.906 --> 05:07.272
Don't worry,
you all will get a GIF

05:07.274 --> 05:09.975
with the best moments
in your inboxes.

05:09.977 --> 05:11.410
Rewind it.

05:11.412 --> 05:12.978
You wanna see the impact again?

05:12.980 --> 05:15.280
I think you can hear Pearson
cry a little bit at the end.

05:15.282 --> 05:17.149
I wanna see the driver.

05:27.527 --> 05:29.261
You know this kid?

05:29.263 --> 05:30.662
I do.

05:30.664 --> 05:32.531
'He was part
of the Nexgeneracers program

05:32.533 --> 05:35.033
a few years back for Out Rescue.

05:35.035 --> 05:37.669
Wait, so you taught him
how to steal cars?

05:40.473 --> 05:42.441
You want me to put
out a warrant?

05:43.676 --> 05:45.043
Yeah.

05:50.383 --> 05:52.384
[engine revving]

06:03.796 --> 06:05.197
[sighs]

06:08.234 --> 06:10.235
Didn't think
you were gonna make it.

06:10.237 --> 06:12.003
Traffic.

06:12.005 --> 06:13.538
15,000 miles on it.

06:13.540 --> 06:15.907
Sells for 400 grand.

06:15.909 --> 06:17.409
No police?

06:17.411 --> 06:19.811
Clean as a new razor blade, yo.

06:19.813 --> 06:21.580
'Cause you know what the boss
will do if you bring the heat.

06:21.582 --> 06:23.115
Yeah, I know, Serge.

06:26.986 --> 06:30.021
20K. Take it or leave it.

06:30.023 --> 06:32.724
It books for almost 400.

06:32.726 --> 06:34.726
You know anyone else that
can move wheels like this?

06:34.728 --> 06:37.129
Come on, Serge,
don't do me like this, man.

06:39.899 --> 06:41.299
19.5.

06:47.173 --> 06:49.007
19.

06:49.009 --> 06:51.510
It's always a pleasure, Junior.

06:51.512 --> 06:53.678
[scoffs]
You got skills, my man.

06:55.281 --> 06:57.082
<i>(female #1)</i>
<i>Nineteen k?</i>

06:57.084 --> 06:59.184
<i>God, you should have got</i>
<i>twice as much.</i>

06:59.186 --> 07:01.353
You wanna argue with Serge, huh?

07:05.958 --> 07:08.527
You almost got
yourself pinched tonight.

07:08.529 --> 07:11.096
- But I didn't.
- But it was stupid.

07:11.098 --> 07:13.365
Why you gotta do stuff like
that, man? It freaks me out.

07:13.367 --> 07:15.767
Look, don't trip, alright?

07:15.769 --> 07:18.470
No cop's gonna ever outdrive me.

07:18.472 --> 07:20.405
Now, floor it, alright?

07:20.407 --> 07:22.274
I'm tryin' to get home
before Tanya wake up.

07:22.276 --> 07:24.910
I am flooring it. This is top
speed for my little baby, okay?

07:24.912 --> 07:28.313
- Hooptie, that's what--
- Shh. She'll hear you.

07:32.785 --> 07:34.186
[keys jingling]

07:45.398 --> 07:48.066
- Did you check first?
- I knew it was you.

07:48.068 --> 07:51.102
- What are you doin' up?
- I recorded "Supergirl."

07:51.104 --> 07:52.904
Can we watch
before I go to school?

07:52.906 --> 07:54.573
- Oh.
- Please?

07:54.575 --> 07:56.775
Okay. Just hold on.

07:56.777 --> 07:59.811
I gotta put
some of this stuff up first.

07:59.813 --> 08:02.380
- You get cereal?
- Of course.

08:04.650 --> 08:06.852
- Multigrain?
- Better for you.

08:06.854 --> 08:08.753
- They're brown.
- We brown.

08:08.755 --> 08:10.755
Ain't nothin' wrong
with being brown, Tanya.

08:10.757 --> 08:13.024
- Ooh, it comes with stickers.
- Mm-hm.

08:16.429 --> 08:18.196
[chuckles]

08:18.198 --> 08:20.532
You finish your homework?

08:20.534 --> 08:22.934
- Tanya.
- 'On the table.'

08:26.606 --> 08:28.573
Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

08:29.675 --> 08:31.710
[sighs]

08:31.712 --> 08:34.079
- 'Hurry up!'
- Alright. I'll be right there.

08:35.615 --> 08:37.682
[indistinct chatter
on police radio]

08:45.658 --> 08:47.626
[intense music]

08:52.198 --> 08:54.199
Dez, what is it?

08:55.868 --> 09:00.071
Um, I'm in a little bit
of trouble, alright?

09:01.541 --> 09:03.475
But everything's gonna be okay.

09:03.477 --> 09:06.845
I'mma figure somethin' out.
You gotta trust me.

09:06.847 --> 09:08.213
[knock on door]

09:08.215 --> 09:09.915
- 'Police, open up!'
- Dez, I'm scared.

09:09.917 --> 09:12.584
Hey. Look at me, alright?

09:12.586 --> 09:15.320
You gotta be strong because
I can't be worrying about you.

09:15.322 --> 09:16.555
[knock on door]

09:16.557 --> 09:19.357
(male #2)
'LAPD. Open the door.'

09:19.359 --> 09:21.860
It's alright, Tanya.
It's, it's alright.

09:21.862 --> 09:23.461
[knock on door]

09:31.537 --> 09:33.271
Hey. Hi, honey.

09:35.174 --> 09:36.575
Oh, baby. You're a savior.

09:36.577 --> 09:37.976
[chuckles]

09:39.779 --> 09:42.581
- I missed you last night.
- Yeah, I just crashed here.

09:42.583 --> 09:44.916
We ran into all kinds
of trouble yesterday.

09:44.918 --> 09:48.253
I know. What's Harvey sayin'?

09:48.255 --> 09:53.258
Well, he thinks
the suspension's not dialed in.

09:53.260 --> 09:56.428
Bulger still thinks
it's the driving.

09:56.430 --> 09:58.430
What do you think?

10:02.602 --> 10:05.303
I don't know.
Maybe Trent's not carrying

10:05.305 --> 10:07.906
enough speed into the corners.

10:07.908 --> 10:09.908
I don't know. God, if I could
just get to the driver's seat--

10:09.910 --> 10:12.844
Oh, you can't do that
to yourself, no.

10:15.214 --> 10:17.549
I just can't get
this team to gel.

10:17.551 --> 10:19.551
It's like they're all speakin'
a different language.

10:19.553 --> 10:21.519
You're letting it consume you.

10:23.623 --> 10:25.624
This is all I am, baby.

10:27.226 --> 10:29.194
If I can't make this work..

10:30.997 --> 10:32.998
...what's left for me?

10:34.233 --> 10:35.467
Hey.

10:37.003 --> 10:39.170
You're Rick Radden.

10:39.172 --> 10:40.672
[scoffs]

10:40.674 --> 10:42.941
Look, I know that
you wanna trust your team

10:42.943 --> 10:44.909
but you need to trust yourself.

10:47.813 --> 10:49.814
Yeah, I hear you, babe.

10:57.023 --> 10:58.523
[sighs]

11:08.267 --> 11:10.435
[scoffs]
Oh, man.

11:12.138 --> 11:14.372
'You come to lecture me?'

11:14.374 --> 11:17.475
- Would it do any good?
- I didn't do anything.

11:17.477 --> 11:20.445
You didn't steal the Rolls
and lead an officer on a chase?

11:20.447 --> 11:22.347
Or you crashed a patrol car.

11:23.516 --> 11:25.116
That sounds like me.

11:25.118 --> 11:28.887
[chuckles]
But, nope. Wasn't me.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.326
Look familiar?

11:35.328 --> 11:39.030
[scoffs]
Yeah. A long time ago now.

11:39.032 --> 11:42.467
You were the smartest,
most talented kid in that bunch.

11:42.469 --> 11:43.702
Remember Richter?

11:43.704 --> 11:47.072
[chuckles]
Yeah, Rick. He sucked.

11:47.074 --> 11:50.675
Well, he's working in a repair
shop down in Crenshaw now.

11:50.677 --> 11:54.012
And, uh, Lin Pao,
he's a detailer.

11:54.014 --> 11:56.514
Drivin' around
in his own mobile unit.

11:56.516 --> 11:57.816
Doin' pretty well
for himself too.

11:57.818 --> 12:01.820
- Great for them.
- It is great for them.

12:01.822 --> 12:04.723
Because they're not sittin' here
with me lookin' at jail time.

12:06.692 --> 12:08.660
I told you, I didn't do nothing.

12:12.398 --> 12:14.432
Well, uh..

12:15.568 --> 12:17.702
...I've got a dash cam video

12:17.704 --> 12:20.972
with you wavin' on it
that says otherwise.

12:25.544 --> 12:27.979
They wanna try you
as an adult, Dez.

12:29.515 --> 12:31.683
That means real jail time.

12:33.519 --> 12:35.754
I can't go to no jail.
I got my sister to look after.

12:35.756 --> 12:38.623
No, you don't anymore.
She been thrown into the system.

12:43.195 --> 12:45.363
No one is helpin' me out there!

12:48.033 --> 12:50.635
I tried to help you, Dez.

12:50.637 --> 12:53.571
I brought you
into the Nexgeneracers.

12:53.573 --> 12:55.840
I tried to give you
a sense of direction.

13:03.315 --> 13:05.316
What can I do to get her back?

13:07.386 --> 13:09.187
I'll do anything.

13:10.956 --> 13:12.290
Please.

13:14.927 --> 13:18.096
Well, I could, um, call
in a favor with the DA.

13:18.098 --> 13:21.099
Maybe he can get you probation.

13:21.101 --> 13:24.102
But you'd have to prove
that you can go straight

13:24.104 --> 13:26.437
and stay employed.

13:26.439 --> 13:28.339
If you can do that

13:28.341 --> 13:30.742
maybe you can get
legal guardianship for her

13:30.744 --> 13:32.911
'when you turn 18,
end of summer.'

13:36.782 --> 13:37.982
Okay.

13:41.987 --> 13:44.422
But who's gonna hire me?

13:44.424 --> 13:46.391
[engine revving]

13:49.628 --> 13:51.262
Well, that sounds like shit.

13:51.264 --> 13:53.531
- Is it the timing?
- No, the timing's fine.

13:53.533 --> 13:55.800
- I think the jetting's off.
- Yeah, I think it's the carb.

13:55.802 --> 13:57.936
I think we gotta pull
the carb again.

13:57.938 --> 13:59.070
Fine, pull it.

14:00.773 --> 14:03.641
Hey, Rick, check it out.
You got some company, man.

14:03.643 --> 14:06.845
- Freeman.
- A little engine trouble?

14:06.847 --> 14:10.315
Ah, nothin' we can't handle.
How you doin'?

14:10.317 --> 14:12.450
You're looking good.

14:12.452 --> 14:14.519
Yeah, yeah.

14:14.521 --> 14:16.454
What's goin' on?

14:16.456 --> 14:18.389
Came by to ask you a favor.

14:18.391 --> 14:20.992
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

14:20.994 --> 14:24.963
Got another Nexgeneracer I was,
uh, hopin' you could take on.

14:24.965 --> 14:26.631
[sighs]
Now's not the best time.

14:26.633 --> 14:30.001
We had kind of a shitty start
to the season and--

14:30.003 --> 14:33.137
Well, the kid's smart.
Knows a lot about cars.

14:33.139 --> 14:35.373
I'm sure he does.
All your kids are great.

14:35.375 --> 14:37.375
It's just, uh..

14:37.377 --> 14:39.043
[sighs]
You know what? Look.

14:39.045 --> 14:41.045
Let me get through the weekend
and I'll call you, okay?

14:41.047 --> 14:43.648
It's a little more
urgent than that.

14:43.650 --> 14:45.183
He's sitting in jail.

14:45.185 --> 14:47.418
You wanna put a criminal
on my team?

14:47.420 --> 14:49.988
I wanna put a criminal,
um, in your house.

14:49.990 --> 14:51.823
What? Come on.

14:51.825 --> 14:52.891
[chuckles]

14:52.893 --> 14:54.859
He needs a guardian.

14:54.861 --> 14:56.561
He doesn't turn 18 till August.

14:56.563 --> 14:58.196
I don't know. I don't know.

14:58.198 --> 15:00.531
Now, the kid's had nothin'
but bad luck.

15:00.533 --> 15:02.834
His mom died of cancer
when he was little.

15:02.836 --> 15:06.604
His dad, killed in a break-in
at his shop two years ago.

15:06.606 --> 15:08.573
And he's managed to take care
of his ten-year-old sister

15:08.575 --> 15:12.010
all by himself ever since.

15:12.012 --> 15:15.113
You can't save
every kid, Freeman.

15:15.115 --> 15:17.916
He got busted for stealing
a car, but he's not a bad kid.

15:17.918 --> 15:20.018
Dash cam video nailed him
when he got a little cocky.

15:20.020 --> 15:21.052
[chuckles]

15:21.054 --> 15:22.587
Here's the footage.

15:22.589 --> 15:25.924
Uh...you should watch it.

15:25.926 --> 15:28.226
Unless this is footage of him
sweeping up a pit

15:28.228 --> 15:31.796
or hauling tires, this might not
be the spot for him.

15:31.798 --> 15:33.798
(Bulger)
'Hey, Rick,
come check this out.'

15:35.100 --> 15:37.068
I gotta go.
I'll take a look at it.

15:37.070 --> 15:38.870
But no promises, okay?

15:44.710 --> 15:47.145
(male announcer)
'That's it for Round 3
of Lucas Oil Off Road.'

15:47.147 --> 15:49.280
'Round 4 starts tomorrow
at 10 a.m. sharp'

15:49.282 --> 15:51.683
'with the Pro Lite trucks.
See you there, folks.'

16:11.270 --> 16:13.237
[sirens blaring]

16:17.776 --> 16:19.744
[tires screeching]

16:26.752 --> 16:28.152
(male #3)
'Oh, shit!'

16:40.666 --> 16:42.066
[chuckles]

17:11.663 --> 17:14.298
You wanna stop and get, like,
a toothbrush or anything?

17:19.238 --> 17:21.339
I'm fine.

17:21.341 --> 17:23.641
Yeah, the captain said we can
swing by your apartment

17:23.643 --> 17:25.710
and grab some stuff if you want.

17:27.479 --> 17:30.548
Look, I don't need no one
taking care of me, alright?

17:32.251 --> 17:34.185
Right.

17:34.187 --> 17:36.754
You got out of jail
all by yourself.

17:57.709 --> 17:59.644
- Hey.
- Hi.

18:02.681 --> 18:04.749
So you must be Dez.

18:04.751 --> 18:08.119
- Hello, Miss Radden.
- Oh, call me Glenda.

18:08.121 --> 18:10.688
Glenda? Like the witch?

18:10.690 --> 18:13.524
- The good witch.
- Uh, yeah, sometimes.

18:13.526 --> 18:14.892
(Rick)
'Come on.'

18:14.894 --> 18:16.594
Wh.. Don't you have
any bags or--

18:16.596 --> 18:18.529
We just came straight
from the station.

18:18.531 --> 18:20.198
Yeah.

18:20.200 --> 18:22.467
Couldn't even get
a toothbrush or anything.

18:23.569 --> 18:26.037
Rick, what's wrong with you?

18:26.039 --> 18:28.039
Come on inside.
We'll get you hooked up.

18:30.776 --> 18:33.811
Can I get you anything
to eat or drink?

18:33.813 --> 18:36.314
Um, I'm fine.

18:36.316 --> 18:39.083
Your room is right around the
corner, first door on the left.

18:39.085 --> 18:40.551
Why don't you go ahead?
I'll meet you in there.

18:40.553 --> 18:41.686
Okay.

18:45.991 --> 18:49.494
Honey, be careful where
you leave the keys, alright?

18:51.330 --> 18:52.630
- You're serious?
- Yeah, I'm serious.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.098
This kid's a car thief, hon.

18:54.100 --> 18:56.067
Well, then he doesn't
need keys, does he?

19:05.844 --> 19:08.079
So, you're okay with this?

19:08.081 --> 19:10.681
Mm, I didn't really
have a choice, did I?

19:10.683 --> 19:13.818
- Well, I asked you.
- Mm, more like you told me.

19:13.820 --> 19:16.621
Ah, I'm not gonna argue with
you, baby. I'm not gonna do it.

19:16.623 --> 19:18.422
Well, maybe you should
go check on him, you know

19:18.424 --> 19:20.391
before he steals
all your underwear.

19:23.462 --> 19:24.595
Hey.

19:26.298 --> 19:27.398
Here.

19:29.101 --> 19:31.135
Thanks.

19:31.137 --> 19:34.472
Look, kid, this isn't a game.

19:34.474 --> 19:37.375
You got a lot to prove to me,
to Freeman

19:37.377 --> 19:40.645
to the damn
California Penal system.

19:40.647 --> 19:43.047
- You ready?
- Yeah, I'm ready, man.

19:43.049 --> 19:46.184
Good. Lights out at 11.
We got a big day tomorrow.

19:47.286 --> 19:49.253
I ain't got no bedtime.

19:50.455 --> 19:51.856
Well, you do now.

19:51.858 --> 19:54.192
'I got a lot of shit on my plate
right now, kid'

19:54.194 --> 19:57.161
and babysittin' you
ain't my top priority.

19:57.163 --> 19:58.963
So, keep your head down
and your mouth shut

19:58.965 --> 20:00.298
and we'll get through
this summer.

20:00.300 --> 20:01.699
Yes, sir.

20:02.968 --> 20:04.936
Now you're gettin' it.

20:32.097 --> 20:34.198
So I'm comin' in,
I'm 30 feet in the air

20:34.200 --> 20:35.700
and I got that
son of a bitch sideways.

20:35.702 --> 20:37.201
'So when I come in and I land'

20:37.203 --> 20:39.270
I'm carrying a lot of speed
around that corner

20:39.272 --> 20:41.105
and they just became
innocent bystanders

20:41.107 --> 20:42.440
seeing the speed I was
carrying through--

20:42.442 --> 20:44.909
Alright, alright,
listen up, everyone.

20:44.911 --> 20:47.845
We're gonna put yesterday's
disaster behind us.

20:47.847 --> 20:50.014
We got qualifying at 11:00.

20:50.016 --> 20:51.983
'I'm gonna need
everyone on point.'

20:53.719 --> 20:56.087
What? What's the problem?

20:56.089 --> 20:57.922
You know there's a black kid
standing behind you, right?

20:59.858 --> 21:03.928
This is Dez Truss. He's one of
Captain Freeman's Nexgeneracers.

21:03.930 --> 21:06.397
He's gonna be workin'
with us this summer.

21:06.399 --> 21:08.432
How you doin'?
I'm Harvey, crew chief.

21:08.434 --> 21:09.900
Yeah.

21:09.902 --> 21:11.869
This is Bulger,
our head mechanic.

21:13.472 --> 21:15.573
- How you doin'?
- Good.

21:15.575 --> 21:18.075
- That's Robbie over there.
- What's up, dude?

21:18.077 --> 21:20.711
Of course, Trent, our driver.

21:20.713 --> 21:22.346
Nexgeneracers, huh?

21:24.449 --> 21:27.251
You know this ain't go-karts,
right, kid?

21:27.253 --> 21:29.553
- Come on, back off, Trent.
- No, no, no, no, no.

21:29.555 --> 21:30.921
Rick, it's a smart move,
you know.

21:30.923 --> 21:32.590
Reachin' out
to the urban demographic.

21:32.592 --> 21:34.458
Maybe get us a few new sponsors.

21:34.460 --> 21:37.561
Philly Blunts or one of those
fancy malt liquor companies.

21:37.563 --> 21:39.430
Yeah, we got plenty
of sponsors, Trent.

21:39.432 --> 21:41.866
You just gotta start winning,
so we can keep 'em.

21:44.236 --> 21:46.137
[scoffs]

21:46.139 --> 21:47.905
Alright, everyone,
let's get our shit together.

21:47.907 --> 21:50.341
I want you to double check
that alignment, Robbie.

21:50.343 --> 21:53.444
Speakin' of shit, Dez,
the, uh, brown water out tubes

21:53.446 --> 21:56.814
clogged on the RV, so, uh,
welcome to Team Radden.

21:59.151 --> 22:02.186
You heard him, Dez.
Head down, mouth shut, hop to.

22:13.532 --> 22:14.965
[grunts]

22:14.967 --> 22:16.033
Eww.

22:17.102 --> 22:18.369
Nice kicks.

22:18.371 --> 22:20.271
Yeah, they were.

22:20.273 --> 22:22.840
Sorry, man, you totally
coulda used these.

22:22.842 --> 22:24.475
[sighs]
The guy's an asshole.

22:24.477 --> 22:25.776
But even though,
he's the face of our team

22:25.778 --> 22:27.945
so we keep him happy.
You got it?

22:27.947 --> 22:30.648
- I got it.
- Hey, look, man, here.

22:30.650 --> 22:32.717
You get this done, I'll get you
some more work in the pit, okay?

22:32.719 --> 22:34.785
I promise, don't worry.
And hey.

22:34.787 --> 22:36.854
Trent ain't got the energy
to be a dick all day.

22:42.828 --> 22:44.662
[engine revving]

22:44.664 --> 22:46.630
Yo, Dez, can you grab me
that gun over there?

22:48.200 --> 22:50.267
No, with the small socket,
the small socket.

22:51.737 --> 22:54.338
- Yeah. Thank you.
- You got it.

22:54.340 --> 22:56.207
[whirring]

22:56.209 --> 22:58.275
Alright, take it out, Trent!

22:59.177 --> 23:01.078
Hey, is the race startin'?

23:01.080 --> 23:02.480
No, man, it's qualifying round.

23:02.482 --> 23:03.848
Seven laps best time

23:03.850 --> 23:05.716
gets pole position
this afternoon.

23:05.718 --> 23:08.018
Stay here. We'll see you later.

23:08.020 --> 23:09.987
<i>(male announcer)</i>
<i>All Group 4 teams to pre-grid.</i>

23:09.989 --> 23:11.956
[engines revving]

23:29.608 --> 23:32.710
We're startin' in tenth.
What was it this time?

23:32.712 --> 23:34.578
Change up the damn tires,
Rick, alright?

23:34.580 --> 23:36.714
It's like I'm driving
out snot out there.

23:36.716 --> 23:39.049
It's not the damn..

23:39.051 --> 23:42.686
[scoffs]
You know, change 'em.

23:42.688 --> 23:43.954
One less thing for him
to complain

23:43.956 --> 23:45.689
about when he loses again.

23:45.691 --> 23:48.125
You heard him, you guys. Let's
get four new Generals on there.

23:48.127 --> 23:50.761
(Bulger)
'Copy that.'

23:50.763 --> 23:54.432
- Wanna help me out with that?
- Now let's get her cleaned up.

23:54.434 --> 23:57.468
(Seaver)
'The dirt continues to fly here
at Glen Helen Raceway'

23:57.470 --> 24:00.137
'as we head into our main event,
the Pro 4 trucks.'

24:00.139 --> 24:03.974
(Arnold)
'So far, this season has started
off as the Carl Renezeder show.'

24:03.976 --> 24:06.777
(male announcer)
'All teams to pre-grid.
All teams to pre-grid.'

24:06.779 --> 24:08.446
'The race is about to begin.'

24:08.448 --> 24:10.781
- You got this, brother.
- Okay. You gotta be safe.

24:14.986 --> 24:17.721
Hey, can I go too?

24:17.723 --> 24:19.990
Clean up the tools first,
then meet us at the hot pits.

24:24.329 --> 24:26.163
(Arnold)
'And Carl Renezeder
will be starting out'

24:26.165 --> 24:28.766
'of Row 2 today as we check out
our starting grid.'

24:28.768 --> 24:30.668
(Seaver)
'Back in Row 5,
Trent Lerion's off'

24:30.670 --> 24:33.404
'to another disappointing start
for Rick Radden's team.'

24:33.406 --> 24:34.905
'There's reports of all kinds'

24:34.907 --> 24:36.807
'of friction
between Lerion and Radden.'

24:36.809 --> 24:38.342
(Arnold)
Well, he's gotta finish
higher than tenth'

24:38.344 --> 24:40.077
'to put an end to those rumors.'

24:40.079 --> 24:42.146
(Seaver)
'And here we go, Round 4.'

24:42.148 --> 24:44.915
'It is on and Kyle LeDuc
is out on the throttle.'

24:44.917 --> 24:46.851
'He needs to stay in front
for 20 laps'

24:46.853 --> 24:49.453
'to take his first victory
of the year.'

24:49.455 --> 24:51.288
You're good. You're good.

24:51.290 --> 24:54.091
You can't come through here
without a wristband.

24:54.093 --> 24:55.593
- I'm crew.
- And I'm Jay-Z.

24:55.595 --> 24:57.361
No wristband, no entry.

25:01.800 --> 25:03.767
(Seaver)
'Trent Lerion's Number 7
Rockstar truck'

25:03.769 --> 25:06.704
'is getting bottled up
in the back of the pack.'

25:06.706 --> 25:09.173
- Clear, Trent, make a move.
- I can't find an opening.

25:12.444 --> 25:13.644
What's his problem?

25:13.646 --> 25:15.613
Don't tell me
it's the damn tires.

25:15.615 --> 25:16.981
How are the tires?

25:16.983 --> 25:18.516
Well, they can't make
this piece of crap truck

25:18.518 --> 25:19.717
'go any faster.'

25:19.719 --> 25:21.719
He says they're good.

25:31.363 --> 25:33.597
[engine revving]

25:42.407 --> 25:44.408
[engines revving]

25:49.681 --> 25:51.415
Oh, shit.

25:53.552 --> 25:55.986
Yeah. It's not go-karts.

26:03.562 --> 26:06.397
(Arnold)
'Renezeder's Lucas Oil truck
is surfing well today.'

26:06.399 --> 26:08.065
'He's run a great race.'

26:08.067 --> 26:09.400
(Seaver)
'And Carl Renezeder takes'

26:09.402 --> 26:11.068
'the checkered flag yet again.'

26:11.070 --> 26:14.038
'Kyle LeDuc in second
and Rob MacCachren in third.'

26:14.040 --> 26:16.073
(Arnold)
'Carl Renezeder,
three wins in a row?'

26:16.075 --> 26:18.108
'A lot of momentum
for your team right now.'

26:18.110 --> 26:19.843
And congratulations.
Another battle out there today

26:19.845 --> 26:21.445
but, uh, you got it done.
Nice job.

26:21.447 --> 26:23.847
(Carl)
'Lucas Oil, General Tire
And Trucks is amazing.'

26:23.849 --> 26:25.583
To be able to win races,
you gotta be able to finish

26:25.585 --> 26:27.785
and you gotta be able
to finish strong.

26:27.787 --> 26:30.187
So, just really wanna give
my hats off to my crew, man.

26:30.189 --> 26:31.689
Those guys are amazing.

26:36.561 --> 26:38.028
Rough first day, huh?

26:41.199 --> 26:43.167
Trent came in eighth.

26:44.235 --> 26:46.403
You good with that?

26:46.405 --> 26:48.606
Yeah, it's not all about
finishing position

26:48.608 --> 26:50.741
and Trent had some fast laps

26:50.743 --> 26:53.010
some good passes and the truck..

26:54.479 --> 26:56.313
[sighs]
No, I'm not good with that.

27:00.118 --> 27:02.486
Top three finishers
go on the podium.

27:02.488 --> 27:05.923
Interviews, TV time..
That's what sponsors want.

27:05.925 --> 27:07.791
Trent ever go to the podium?

27:07.793 --> 27:09.593
Well, he used to all the time.

27:09.595 --> 27:11.996
That's why I paid him
the big bucks to get him here.

27:13.565 --> 27:16.767
But he only made two podiums
last season.

27:16.769 --> 27:19.970
- I'm guessing that's a problem.
- Oh, yeah.

27:19.972 --> 27:23.307
- Yeah.
- When is the next race?

27:23.309 --> 27:25.309
Two weeks. Lake Elsinore.

27:27.078 --> 27:28.245
Got it.

27:30.982 --> 27:32.750
Hey, you wanna see
something cool?

27:40.091 --> 27:42.860
[chuckles]

27:42.862 --> 27:44.862
- Whoa.
- You know what that is?

27:46.464 --> 27:48.932
- GMC Syclone.
- Yeah.

27:48.934 --> 27:51.869
Turbo V6. All wheel drive.

27:51.871 --> 27:54.104
Fastest American car in '91.

27:54.106 --> 27:57.207
Yeah, that car won me a lot
of money back in the day.

27:57.209 --> 27:59.109
How 'bout this?
You know what that is?

27:59.111 --> 28:03.213
Red Dragon, ESX STI.
Limited edition.

28:03.215 --> 28:04.815
450 horsepower.

28:04.817 --> 28:07.117
Yeah, plus 100 shot of nitrous.

28:07.119 --> 28:11.288
It's fast, but not as fast
as the Hellcat.

28:11.290 --> 28:14.058
Mm, maybe we should find out.

28:14.060 --> 28:15.459
[chuckles]

28:16.461 --> 28:18.362
Oh, snap.

28:18.364 --> 28:21.231
(Rick)
Yeah, it seems
like a lifetime ago.

28:21.233 --> 28:24.968
Damn. You were a baller.

28:24.970 --> 28:26.403
Yeah.

28:26.405 --> 28:28.739
Why you ain't still drivin'?

28:28.741 --> 28:32.476
I had a little accident.
Can't go 20 laps anymore.

28:34.012 --> 28:35.979
How many races you win?

28:37.749 --> 28:39.149
Most of 'em.

28:43.021 --> 28:46.390
Alright, the show's over.
Let's go.

29:02.407 --> 29:03.807
[Dez chuckles]

29:06.444 --> 29:07.878
When your spotter tells you

29:07.880 --> 29:10.047
Rick Radden's behind you,
uh, hold on.

29:10.049 --> 29:13.951
(male #4 on video)
'After 12 years, 3 championships
and 109 total wins'

29:13.953 --> 29:17.221
'the name Rick Radden was
synonymous with short course.'

29:17.223 --> 29:19.022
'His aggressive style
drew both praise'

29:19.024 --> 29:21.291
'and criticism
from his fellow drivers.'

29:21.293 --> 29:22.626
He's somebody that's not, uh

29:22.628 --> 29:24.294
not real high on my list,
you know?

29:24.296 --> 29:25.696
(Myan)
'He's not afraid
to drive through you.'

29:25.698 --> 29:27.131
You just gotta be tough
when you're at him.

29:27.133 --> 29:28.632
He's got the best crew
out there.

29:28.634 --> 29:30.200
'If I had his money, his team'

29:30.202 --> 29:32.069
his ride, I'd smoke him.

29:32.071 --> 29:34.204
(male #4)
'He was on his way
to a fourth championship'

29:34.206 --> 29:36.774
'until this moment in 2012.'

29:36.776 --> 29:40.043
(Seaver)
'Rick Radden and Creed are going
door to door into that jump.'

29:40.045 --> 29:41.912
- 'Oh!'
- 'Oh, no!'

29:41.914 --> 29:44.581
(Arnold)
'Radden goes for a nasty ride.'

29:44.583 --> 29:47.084
'What a vicious barrel roll.
Let's hope he's okay.'

29:47.086 --> 29:49.787
'They're pulling Radden out.
He's having trouble moving.'

29:49.789 --> 29:51.789
'This could be a career ender
for Rick Radden.'

29:51.791 --> 29:53.924
(Myan)
'Nobody, uh, likes to see
anything like that happen.'

29:53.926 --> 29:56.326
Uh, uh, we weren't the closest,
uh, that's for sure

29:56.328 --> 29:58.395
but that, that was
a tough one, but..

29:58.397 --> 30:00.497
'That, that guy,
that guy's tough..'

30:07.172 --> 30:09.740
<i>(male #4)</i>
<i>Radden returned to short course</i>
<i>last year as a team owner</i>

30:09.742 --> 30:12.176
<i>and, so far,</i>
<i>it hasn't gone very well.</i>

30:12.178 --> 30:14.178
Rick, do you consider
your first year as a team owner

30:14.180 --> 30:16.446
a failure?

30:16.448 --> 30:20.184
No, I, I wouldn't use
the, the term failure, no.

30:20.186 --> 30:24.087
Do you think 2017 will be the
breakout year for your team?

30:24.089 --> 30:27.357
Well, we're just gonna take it
one day at a time, and, um..

30:27.359 --> 30:28.859
we think you're gonna see
some good rides

30:28.861 --> 30:30.694
out of Trent Lerion this season.

30:30.696 --> 30:33.697
- 'Thank you, Rick.'
- Thank you.

30:33.699 --> 30:35.465
Alright, Dez, it's gonna be
super easy since you already

30:35.467 --> 30:37.701
know cars. You got your master
power right here, alright?

30:37.703 --> 30:40.504
Turn it on, engage the fuel pump
right there.

30:40.506 --> 30:43.040
Engage the ignition, prime it.

30:43.042 --> 30:45.209
See the pressure
go up right there?

30:45.211 --> 30:46.276
Then you just start right here.

30:46.278 --> 30:48.245
[engine revving]

30:50.215 --> 30:51.949
Alright, man, just bring it
forward nice and slow.

30:51.951 --> 30:53.350
Don't punch it.

30:55.053 --> 30:56.253
'There ya go.'

31:01.693 --> 31:03.660
(Rob MacCachren)
'Um, but after the fact
we found out that'

31:03.662 --> 31:05.896
'there was a lot of mud packed
in the passenger side wheels'

31:05.898 --> 31:07.531
'which is probably
the vibration.'

31:07.533 --> 31:09.233
We think we had a little bit
of a carburetor issue

31:09.235 --> 31:11.802
which, uh, caused a lack
of power and the engine oil..

31:11.804 --> 31:13.503
(Trent)
'Just listen to what
I'm sayin', man.'

31:13.505 --> 31:15.973
Listen here,
by increasing the front bias

31:15.975 --> 31:17.741
we'll get you more traction
in the turns.

31:17.743 --> 31:20.377
Yeah, until I hit a rut and
then I'm riding a tilt-a-whirl--

31:20.379 --> 31:22.145
How about you just take
a couple of test laps, huh?

31:22.147 --> 31:23.247
'You can do that?'

31:23.249 --> 31:24.715
Maybe you could drive the truck

31:24.717 --> 31:26.350
and I'll go maul a village.

31:26.352 --> 31:28.418
- Listen--
- Okay, hey, hey!

31:28.420 --> 31:30.087
(Harvey)
'Hey, Rick, I got this.
I'll take care of this.'

31:30.089 --> 31:31.488
I got it.

31:32.590 --> 31:34.758
'We're gonna decrease the bias.'

31:34.760 --> 31:37.194
(Bulger)
Okay. Sure.

31:37.196 --> 31:38.729
- Hey.
- 'Hi.'

31:38.731 --> 31:40.197
Hey, how are you doin'?

31:40.199 --> 31:42.766
Are they taking care
of you over there?

31:42.768 --> 31:44.768
(Tanya)
'I miss you, Dez.'

31:46.738 --> 31:48.005
I know.

31:49.540 --> 31:52.609
[sighs]
I miss you too.

31:52.611 --> 31:55.512
But hey, I'm gonna come see you.

31:55.514 --> 31:57.581
- In two weeks.
- 'Okay.'

32:02.453 --> 32:04.021
Where we at?

32:04.023 --> 32:06.690
Best lap time so far is 50.522.

32:06.692 --> 32:08.592
Trent has us starting in ninth
place later this afternoon.

32:08.594 --> 32:09.626
Damn it!

32:09.628 --> 32:11.628
[engines revving]

32:13.231 --> 32:15.832
Harvey, I'm not feelin' it.

32:18.803 --> 32:21.171
Uh, hit this next corner hard.
See if that rattles her a bit.

32:28.279 --> 32:31.548
Well, it rattled me
a little bit.

32:31.550 --> 32:33.583
Just keep runnin' on all fours.
Do what you can.

32:33.585 --> 32:35.485
We'll check it out later
before the race.

32:35.487 --> 32:37.721
- He's not feelin' it.
- Does he ever?

32:48.733 --> 32:50.400
Damn it!

32:50.402 --> 32:53.070
Hasn't anybody here
worked on a truck, anyone?

32:53.072 --> 32:54.638
Take it easy, brother.
We'll get her ready.

32:54.640 --> 32:55.672
When?

32:57.175 --> 32:59.176
No, he's right.

32:59.178 --> 33:01.745
What is it with this team?

33:01.747 --> 33:04.781
We're never on the damn podium.
The truck is a mess.

33:04.783 --> 33:06.650
If we don't get our heads
out of our asses

33:06.652 --> 33:09.353
we're gonna lose the sponsors,
we're gonna lose our team.

33:09.355 --> 33:12.789
I want this truck running
like a winner by race time!

33:12.791 --> 33:14.691
Alright! Let's do it.
Come on.

33:14.693 --> 33:16.460
Open her up, man.

33:16.462 --> 33:18.161
Harvey, what've you got?
You got somethin' for me?

33:18.163 --> 33:19.696
(Harvey)
Uh, we could try lockin'
the differential

33:19.698 --> 33:21.264
between the front
and rear wheel.

33:21.266 --> 33:23.100
- 'Didn't we already try that?'
- 'I thought we did.'

33:23.102 --> 33:24.768
- But it keeps slippin'.
- Why? Wh-why is it slipping?

33:24.770 --> 33:26.370
I don't know,
I'm not gonna know that

33:26.372 --> 33:28.372
until I get it up
and I run diagnostics.

33:28.374 --> 33:29.973
Bulger, what've you got?

33:29.975 --> 33:32.376
Boss, there's nothin'
we haven't already tried.

33:32.378 --> 33:34.077
[sighs]
Great.

33:36.014 --> 33:38.015
We could try increasing
the differential.

33:40.184 --> 33:43.487
Dez, you got somethin'?

33:43.489 --> 33:46.223
You're gonna listen to your
shop boy now? Jesus, Rick!

33:46.225 --> 33:49.559
You guys are as useful as a dog
takin' a shit on the engine.

33:49.561 --> 33:52.362
So, yeah, I'm gonna listen
to the shop boy.

33:52.364 --> 33:54.898
What do you got, buddy?
Give it to me, speak up.

33:54.900 --> 33:57.901
Okay, uh, well..

33:57.903 --> 33:59.536
...why don't you try
and go the other way?

33:59.538 --> 34:00.971
What do you mean?

34:00.973 --> 34:02.706
Instead of, like,
lockin' the differential

34:02.708 --> 34:04.307
why don't you open it?

34:04.309 --> 34:06.076
No, kid, no.

34:06.078 --> 34:07.911
We'd lose all our traction.

34:07.913 --> 34:09.913
'He's gonna slide
into stands on every turn.'

34:09.915 --> 34:12.382
MacCachren ran three seasons
on an open differential.

34:12.384 --> 34:14.351
Got him a lot of podiums.

34:14.353 --> 34:16.586
(Harvey)
Yeah, he had a completely
different driving style.

34:16.588 --> 34:18.855
I'm sure Mr. Lerion
can make the adjustment.

34:18.857 --> 34:20.490
He's gonna tell me
how to drive now.

34:20.492 --> 34:22.159
'Keep your dog on a leash,
would you?'

34:22.161 --> 34:25.028
Just listen, man.
The kid's got a point, okay?

34:25.030 --> 34:27.364
What we lose in traction,
we're gonna get in speed

34:27.366 --> 34:28.999
when we come out of those turns.

34:29.001 --> 34:30.600
You know, I'm right here, guys.

34:30.602 --> 34:32.436
I'm right here.
Don't I get a say in this?

34:32.438 --> 34:34.838
The floor is yours. Speak up.

34:38.509 --> 34:40.343
Fix the truck, Rick. Alright?

34:40.345 --> 34:42.312
I can drive it
if you idiots can fix it.

34:45.750 --> 34:47.717
Alright, let's do it.

34:47.719 --> 34:49.786
Let's do it, come on.

34:49.788 --> 34:53.623
(Seaver)
'We're racing Round 5,
Lake Elsinore Motorsports Park.'

34:53.625 --> 34:57.027
'Kyle LeDuc leads with Carl
Renezeder hot on his tail'

34:57.029 --> 34:58.562
'and Trent Lerion
in third place.'

34:58.564 --> 34:59.863
(Harvey)
'How are you feelin'?'

34:59.865 --> 35:01.231
Like driving
a broken shopping cart

35:01.233 --> 35:02.699
through a river of piss.

35:02.701 --> 35:05.102
- He's not lovin' it.
- Well, we're in third.

35:05.104 --> 35:06.169
He's doin' somethin' right.

35:08.606 --> 35:11.041
(Seaver)
'Let's take a look at this
battle for third place.'

35:11.043 --> 35:12.909
'Eric Barron's hawking.
Trent Lerion'

35:12.911 --> 35:15.779
'trying to get around him for
that final spot on the podium.'

35:15.781 --> 35:17.280
(Harvey)
Trent, you're doin' really good.

35:17.282 --> 35:18.915
Get some distance
between you and Barron.

35:18.917 --> 35:20.917
Get ready.
He's gonna speed by you.

35:20.919 --> 35:23.120
We're runnin' out of time.

35:23.122 --> 35:25.489
(Arnold)
'LeDuc and Renezeder
are really bangin' it out'

35:25.491 --> 35:28.058
'and Lerion's doing his best
to hold off Barron for third.'

35:28.060 --> 35:31.261
(Seaver)
'Oh, Lerion barely moves on
as they come out of Turn 2.'

35:31.263 --> 35:33.230
He's gotta accelerate more
into the turns.

35:35.633 --> 35:37.934
He needs to come in harder
on the turns.

35:37.936 --> 35:40.904
I'm not payin' him to
participate. I want that podium!

35:40.906 --> 35:42.739
Come on, man.
Put some slam on that throttle.

35:42.741 --> 35:44.708
This one's yours, buddy.

35:48.846 --> 35:50.747
(male announcer #1)
'Well, it looks like
Lerion's got another gear.'

35:50.749 --> 35:53.483
'He's finally opening up some
space between him and Barron.'

35:53.485 --> 35:55.152
Come on!

35:55.154 --> 35:57.320
'And as they battle
coming into the checkered flag'

35:57.322 --> 36:00.423
'Carl Renezeder barely holds off
Kyle LeDuc for the win'

36:00.425 --> 36:03.160
'and look at this,
Trent Lerion in third.'

36:03.162 --> 36:04.694
- Whoo!
- Alright!

36:04.696 --> 36:06.630
Oh, my God, man!

36:06.632 --> 36:08.598
- Finally. Finally.
- Finally.

36:18.843 --> 36:20.810
[laughing]

36:20.812 --> 36:22.479
You did it, Trent!

36:22.481 --> 36:24.814
Ooh-ah!

36:24.816 --> 36:26.783
[crowd applauding]

36:29.720 --> 36:32.689
(male announcer #1)
'In third place, Trent Lerion.'

36:32.691 --> 36:34.624
[crowd cheering]

36:34.626 --> 36:37.194
'In second place, Kyle LeDuc.'

36:38.863 --> 36:41.298
'And our champion,
Carl Renezeder.'

36:41.300 --> 36:44.501
Hold up,
only crew and press allowed.

36:44.503 --> 36:46.536
I'm with Team Radden.

36:46.538 --> 36:50.307
- See?
- I don't give a shit.

36:50.309 --> 36:53.143
(male announcer #1)
'Let's give 'em
another hand, folks.'

36:53.145 --> 36:54.544
Alright, Trent.

36:55.846 --> 36:58.548
What's the problem, man?
The kid's with us.

36:58.550 --> 37:00.550
And he won us the race.

37:01.886 --> 37:04.688
So open the gate.

37:04.690 --> 37:06.856
- Whatever.
- Thank you.

37:06.858 --> 37:08.992
(male announcer #2)
Alright, once again,
now we got Trent Lerion here

37:08.994 --> 37:10.527
in third place. We're gonna
go over and talk to him.

37:10.529 --> 37:12.896
Trent, you know,
this has been a long time coming

37:12.898 --> 37:14.731
'back in the podium
for Team Radden.'

37:14.733 --> 37:16.099
I can tell by the smile
on your face

37:16.101 --> 37:17.500
you're just stoked to be here.

37:17.502 --> 37:19.736
Yeah, it feels, uh,
feels really good.

37:19.738 --> 37:22.239
You know, it's uh,
it's been a long overdue time

37:22.241 --> 37:24.541
to get this fantastic Rockstar
truck up on this podium.

37:24.543 --> 37:27.577
Um, I pulled some great moves
today, but, uh

37:27.579 --> 37:30.146
I gotta give a shout out
to one guy who made this happen.

37:32.016 --> 37:34.517
Harvey Pearson, our crew chief.

37:34.519 --> 37:37.587
Yeah, brother.
Yeah, we did it. I'm back.

37:37.589 --> 37:39.923
And tomorrow, we're gonna be
on top of this podium.

37:39.925 --> 37:42.092
So I'm comin' for you, Carl.

37:42.094 --> 37:44.294
(male announcer #2)
'Trent Lerion, everybody,
third place.'

37:48.899 --> 37:50.867
What are you doin', kid?
Come on.

37:54.739 --> 37:57.540
So, where did you learn
so much about cars?

38:00.745 --> 38:03.146
My pops owned a shop
in Inglewood.

38:05.249 --> 38:07.217
Grew up in that shop.

38:08.886 --> 38:11.588
[engine revving]

38:11.590 --> 38:13.923
Yeah. You hear that!

38:13.925 --> 38:16.259
Sounds like she's runnin'
on tiger bend.

38:16.261 --> 38:17.594
Makes me wanna drink
dragon blood

38:17.596 --> 38:18.828
and do karate
on a mountain, man!

38:18.830 --> 38:20.330
[laughing]

38:20.332 --> 38:22.265
Alright, let's get her in
and check her out.

38:22.267 --> 38:23.967
Hey, Dez.

38:23.969 --> 38:26.336
You get to clean every speck
of mud off this vehicle.

38:26.338 --> 38:28.338
[laughing]

38:29.407 --> 38:30.774
(Dez)
'Great.'

38:30.776 --> 38:32.309
[engine sputters]

38:35.513 --> 38:37.514
It ain't goin' into gear.

38:39.650 --> 38:41.651
Had to jinx us, huh?

38:48.993 --> 38:50.360
[groaning]

38:50.362 --> 38:52.329
(Trent)
'Ah, shit!'

38:52.331 --> 38:55.532
- Yo, you okay?
- No, man, that really hurt.

38:56.267 --> 38:57.500
Let me see.

38:57.502 --> 38:59.135
Ah, I just jammed it
with the wrench.

38:59.137 --> 39:01.204
I finished the assembly though.

39:01.206 --> 39:03.006
Can you drive?

39:03.008 --> 39:05.342
I can steer, but not to shift.
This thing's throbbing already.

39:05.344 --> 39:07.677
- Oh, it's that bad?
- It hurts, dude.

39:09.680 --> 39:13.116
Well, if you can't drive,
the kid could do it.

39:13.118 --> 39:15.719
- Rick is that a good idea?
- Yeah, yeah, he could do it.

39:17.388 --> 39:18.855
Go on, kid, suit up.

39:24.795 --> 39:26.363
Right, there.

39:26.365 --> 39:29.766
- Okay, all set.
- Alright, kid, let's do it.

39:31.035 --> 39:33.036
[engine revving]

39:39.844 --> 39:42.011
Shift it to second,
real smooth.

39:42.013 --> 39:43.980
'We're not doin' any jumps'.'

39:46.550 --> 39:48.585
Alright, now to third.

39:55.993 --> 39:58.595
Okay, now. Shift back down
to the second for the hairpin.

40:02.500 --> 40:03.933
Goin' pretty good.

40:03.935 --> 40:06.069
Let's see how he does
under load.

40:06.071 --> 40:07.904
Alright, kid,
you got a straightaway comin'.

40:07.906 --> 40:10.240
'I want you to go three-quarters
throttle to third'

40:10.242 --> 40:12.275
and then brake before the jump.

40:12.277 --> 40:13.610
I can handle the jump.

40:13.612 --> 40:15.044
No, no, kid, you gotta learn
how to launch it

40:15.046 --> 40:16.379
so you don't nosedive.

40:16.381 --> 40:18.348
[engine revving]

40:31.061 --> 40:33.029
Hey, slow down, kid.

40:34.465 --> 40:36.032
Slow down!

40:43.808 --> 40:46.409
Kinda like that, boss?

40:46.411 --> 40:48.945
Yeah, kinda like that.

40:48.947 --> 40:50.647
(Dez)
Don't worry. man.

40:50.649 --> 40:52.649
In my former line of work

40:52.651 --> 40:55.485
it was also important
not to damage the product.

40:58.155 --> 40:59.456
(Bulger)
'Looking pretty strong.'

40:59.458 --> 41:01.257
Might wanna open her up
a little bit.

41:01.259 --> 41:03.560
See her full throttle.

41:03.562 --> 41:05.895
Hey, kid, do you think
you can do it again..

41:05.897 --> 41:07.430
'only a little faster
this time?'

41:07.432 --> 41:09.432
Hey, you got it, boss.

41:09.434 --> 41:11.100
Remember, I only got one truck.

41:11.102 --> 41:13.069
[engine revving]

41:25.015 --> 41:27.050
Not bad. Not bad.

41:28.452 --> 41:30.286
It's shiftin' clean, boss.

41:30.288 --> 41:32.922
'Up and down.'

41:32.924 --> 41:35.091
Hey, Dez.
Why don't you take another lap?

41:36.460 --> 41:38.428
What? She's not
even warmed up yet.

41:44.835 --> 41:46.836
[engine revving]

41:49.640 --> 41:51.007
Where are you going?

41:51.009 --> 41:53.443
Nice control, kid. Nice control.

41:53.445 --> 41:55.411
[engine revving]

42:04.522 --> 42:06.456
55.2.

42:06.458 --> 42:09.225
Shit, man, that ain't half bad.

42:09.227 --> 42:11.227
[engine revving]

42:14.565 --> 42:15.598
Alright.

42:17.001 --> 42:18.034
Nice.

42:21.372 --> 42:23.206
[clamoring]

42:24.675 --> 42:25.808
- Take it easy.
- I got it, I got it.

42:25.810 --> 42:27.043
Don't touch my truck, man.

42:27.045 --> 42:28.878
It's my truck
and I told him to drive

42:28.880 --> 42:30.680
because you're too busy
partying.

42:30.682 --> 42:32.015
- No, no.
- Chill, chill.

42:32.017 --> 42:34.083
Settle down, take it easy.

42:34.085 --> 42:35.885
Alright, Rick.
How 'bout this, alright?

42:35.887 --> 42:37.887
The black prick
touches my truck again

42:37.889 --> 42:40.423
and you find a new driver.
How 'bout that?

42:45.429 --> 42:47.630
- You alright?
- Yeah, man. Talk to him.

43:05.616 --> 43:08.484
- Anyone hear anything?
- Nope.

43:09.954 --> 43:11.754
I'm callin' him again.

43:11.756 --> 43:13.022
(male announcer)
'Final call for qualifying.'

43:13.024 --> 43:14.591
'All drivers to pre-grid.'

43:14.593 --> 43:17.627
Alright, someone go out
and find his ass.

43:17.629 --> 43:20.797
Yo, his ass is here.
Robbie, will you grab my suit?

43:20.799 --> 43:23.066
You got two minutes to qualify.

43:23.068 --> 43:25.802
Relax, old man, alright.
Winners need their beauty sleep.

43:25.804 --> 43:27.804
You didn't win, idiot.

43:31.075 --> 43:34.310
And I hear you were out
till 5:00 a.m.

43:34.312 --> 43:36.312
You look like shit.

43:36.314 --> 43:38.715
- You stink of Jager.
- 'You smelling me now?'

43:38.717 --> 43:41.084
I didn't have time to shower.
Back off, Rick.

43:41.086 --> 43:43.119
Are you still drunk?

43:43.121 --> 43:45.088
He's drunk.

43:45.090 --> 43:47.056
Maybe you don't remember
being in your 20s, buddy.

43:47.058 --> 43:48.725
- But I process that shit.
- Oh, yeah?

43:48.727 --> 43:50.259
You wanna take a breathalyzer
and prove it?

43:50.261 --> 43:51.894
He's gonna be fine, boss.
He's gonna be fine.

43:51.896 --> 43:54.297
- Let's just get ready to roll.
- Yeah, boss.

43:54.299 --> 43:55.598
- Chill out.
- Whoa, whoa.

43:55.600 --> 43:57.567
[clamoring]

43:59.069 --> 44:00.903
Don't you ever
put your hand on me!

44:00.905 --> 44:02.805
Try to picture, pal. Alright.

44:02.807 --> 44:04.574
You want podiums?
You want TV time?

44:04.576 --> 44:07.744
Get used to this face.
'Cause it is Team Radden.

44:07.746 --> 44:09.912
Not anymore. You're fired.

44:09.914 --> 44:13.016
Rick, whoa, hey, Rick.
Come on, man, use your brain.

44:13.018 --> 44:14.684
Hey, we gotta get a truck
in this race.

44:14.686 --> 44:16.452
We're gonna lose
our series points.

44:16.454 --> 44:19.122
What points? A bunch
of bottom-half finishes.

44:19.124 --> 44:20.189
Who gives a shit?

44:20.191 --> 44:21.791
You really wanna do this, Rick?

44:21.793 --> 44:23.926
- Yeah, I do.
- Okay.

44:23.928 --> 44:26.295
Kiss your sponsors goodbye, pal.

44:26.297 --> 44:29.298
You're gonna be back to living
off your wife by tomorrow.

44:29.300 --> 44:31.267
Get out of my pit.

44:31.269 --> 44:33.836
You were always holdin' me back
anyway, old man.

44:33.838 --> 44:35.672
<i>Adios, succos.</i>

44:37.207 --> 44:39.208
What the hell was that?

44:44.481 --> 44:47.183
(Rick)
'What? What are you doin'?'

44:47.185 --> 44:49.485
What, you want out too?

44:49.487 --> 44:50.887
Outta what?

44:50.889 --> 44:52.555
We're done.
Qualifying started.

44:52.557 --> 44:54.490
Well, you don't need
to qualify to race.

44:54.492 --> 44:55.825
Race?

44:55.827 --> 44:58.127
- We don't got a driver.
- Yeah, we do.

45:03.133 --> 45:05.134
The kid.

45:05.136 --> 45:07.336
- Wait, what?
- You could do this, kid.

45:07.338 --> 45:09.172
No, no, no.
Last night was great and all

45:09.174 --> 45:11.708
but that was an open track.
This is the real deal, guys.

45:11.710 --> 45:15.878
You wanna put a shop boy in a
Pro 4 truck with no seat time.

45:15.880 --> 45:18.381
He's had a good five, six
minutes on the track.

45:18.383 --> 45:22.485
- Yeah, seven at least.
- Jesus, Rick.

45:22.487 --> 45:26.055
- You lost your mind, man.
- Hey, look, this is happening.

45:26.057 --> 45:29.058
You're gonna join us or you
gonna go off with your boy?

45:29.060 --> 45:30.560
It's your call.

45:36.200 --> 45:38.468
I don't want my name
anywhere near this train, Rick.

45:41.371 --> 45:45.408
Oh, this is great, huh?
This is, this is good.

45:48.178 --> 45:49.579
Anyone else?

45:51.248 --> 45:52.648
Bulger?

45:54.184 --> 45:57.353
Alright,
let's get this rig ready.

45:57.355 --> 45:59.155
Come on, man.
Let's get you suited up.

46:04.394 --> 46:07.163
[dramatic music]

46:16.306 --> 46:18.307
Looking good.

46:18.309 --> 46:20.443
Hey, kid, look,
I had to lie a little.

46:20.445 --> 46:23.446
I told the officials
you raced short track in Mexico.

46:23.448 --> 46:25.815
- Mexico?
- Just roll with it if they ask.

46:25.817 --> 46:27.650
- Alright.
- Alright, look, just..

46:27.652 --> 46:29.786
Keep it on all fours
for the first 12 laps

46:29.788 --> 46:31.120
and then we'll take it
from there.

46:31.122 --> 46:33.256
Alright.

46:33.258 --> 46:36.225
Look, you got skills.

46:36.227 --> 46:37.627
I know it.

46:37.629 --> 46:40.129
Freeman knew it too.

46:40.131 --> 46:42.331
I think that's why
he sent you to me.

46:44.468 --> 46:45.868
You got this.

46:48.305 --> 46:49.505
Alright.

46:52.609 --> 46:55.311
[retches]

46:55.313 --> 46:57.680
Attaboy! Lighten the load.

46:59.917 --> 47:03.352
Alright. Head down, mouth shut,
hop to, Dez.

47:10.694 --> 47:12.962
(Seaver)
'The big news as we look
at our starting grid'

47:12.964 --> 47:15.865
'is that Trent Lerion is
unavailable for today's race.'

47:15.867 --> 47:18.301
'And get this,
Rick Radden has replaced him'

47:18.303 --> 47:20.670
'with 17-year-old Dez Truss.'

47:20.672 --> 47:24.640
'Apparently,
he's raced down in Mexico.'

47:24.642 --> 47:28.177
Alright, now we'll start in last
row 'cause we didn't qualify.

47:28.179 --> 47:30.146
'That's okay.
That's a good thing.'

47:30.148 --> 47:31.981
'Give you some space
to warm up.'

47:31.983 --> 47:33.649
<i>Si, senor.</i>

47:33.651 --> 47:35.284
(Seaver)
'It's time to sling some dirt'

47:35.286 --> 47:38.321
'with big horsepower
and all four wheels diggin'.'

47:38.323 --> 47:40.690
- Here we go.
- Hell, yeah.

47:40.692 --> 47:43.159
- 'The green flag is up.'
- Stay on all fours.

47:43.161 --> 47:46.062
(Seaver)
'And we are green,
green, green.'

47:46.064 --> 47:48.598
[engine revving]

47:58.008 --> 48:00.476
Oh, I can't see a thing.

48:01.845 --> 48:03.946
- Oh, shit.
- You okay, kid?

48:05.983 --> 48:07.583
Like a pinball.

48:07.585 --> 48:08.885
(Rick)
'Yeah, you'll get used to that.'

48:10.254 --> 48:12.521
That's it. Hang back.

48:12.523 --> 48:14.724
Watch their lines.
Get to know the track.

48:16.493 --> 48:18.227
(Seaver)
'Bringing up the rear
in the Number 7'

48:18.229 --> 48:20.596
'Rockstar truck
is the new Team Radden driver.'

48:20.598 --> 48:22.598
(Arnold)
'I don't know what
the Spanish word is for dirt'

48:22.600 --> 48:25.868
'but he's gonna eat
a lot of it here today.'

48:25.870 --> 48:28.537
Well, at least the truck's
still holdin' up.

48:28.539 --> 48:30.840
Yeah, no shit.
He's goin' 10 miles an hour.

48:46.857 --> 48:49.292
(Seaver)
'Barron in the white, red
and orange goin' to the bottom.'

48:49.294 --> 48:51.227
'Kyle LeDuc in the black
on the outside.'

48:51.229 --> 48:53.529
(Arnold)
'Oh, oh, contact, huge move.'

48:53.531 --> 48:56.432
'How did Kyle save that?'

48:56.434 --> 48:58.401
Okay, let's see
if you can make a move.

48:58.403 --> 49:00.436
'Stay on his back porch
until the turn.'

49:02.306 --> 49:05.308
- Then take a line inside him.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

49:05.310 --> 49:07.743
(Seaver)
'Now, look at this, at the back
of the track, Dez Truss'

49:07.745 --> 49:10.913
'our newcomer, looking into make
a move on Josh Merrell.'

49:10.915 --> 49:13.716
'Oh, and there he goes.'

49:13.718 --> 49:15.985
Way to go, Dez.
Keep it together.

49:15.987 --> 49:18.087
(Seaver)
'And Truss passes him
on the inside.'

49:18.089 --> 49:20.790
(Arnold)
'I don't think that's gonna sit
too well with Josh Merrell.'

49:23.660 --> 49:26.128
Hey, I can take this next guy
right here.

49:26.130 --> 49:28.798
Okay, watch your six.
Merrell's coming back for you.

49:33.937 --> 49:35.037
Oh!

49:36.940 --> 49:38.074
Oh!

49:41.445 --> 49:43.846
Oh!

49:43.848 --> 49:46.682
Okay, go, go, go, kid.
The truck's live.

49:46.684 --> 49:48.818
Oh, God!

49:48.820 --> 49:50.753
Hey, w-w-what about Merrell?

49:50.755 --> 49:52.621
(Rick)
'That was nothing.
He's fine too.'

49:52.623 --> 49:55.358
- Nothin'?
- Yeah, welcome to Pro 4, kid.

49:55.360 --> 49:56.959
(Seaver)
'Oh, that crash
took Merrell out'

49:56.961 --> 49:58.594
'but Dez Truss continues on.'

49:58.596 --> 50:01.163
- Alright.
- 'And the white flag is out.'

50:01.165 --> 50:03.666
- 'This is the final lap.'
- Alright, last lap.

50:03.668 --> 50:07.269
(Rick)
'Pretend it's the Wolves
and the 5-O are closing in.'

50:07.271 --> 50:08.704
Yeah, I got it.

50:09.373 --> 50:11.574
[engine revving]

50:21.818 --> 50:25.421
(Seaver)
'And that makes six consecutive
wins for Carl Renezeder.'

50:28.892 --> 50:32.862
'And last to cross the line
