that I would pick 'em up.

1:06:59.983 --> 1:07:02.684
So, I don't wanna leave here
without 'em.

1:07:02.686 --> 1:07:05.286
Suit yourself, babe.

1:07:05.288 --> 1:07:06.888
Alright. Bye, love.

1:07:17.533 --> 1:07:19.367
Well, that explains a lot.

1:07:20.903 --> 1:07:22.537
[shutter clangs]

1:07:28.411 --> 1:07:31.046
[dramatic music]

1:07:31.048 --> 1:07:33.882
Go, there.
In the office.

1:07:35.818 --> 1:07:38.720
[indistinct chatter]

1:07:38.722 --> 1:07:40.121
Slash every tire!

1:08:07.116 --> 1:08:10.685
Okay, that's it. Let's go!
Come on, move it!

1:08:10.687 --> 1:08:12.153
Move it, come on!

1:08:18.027 --> 1:08:19.527
Come on. Let's go.

1:08:21.197 --> 1:08:23.932
[intense music]

1:09:05.174 --> 1:09:07.842
[machine beeping]

1:09:07.844 --> 1:09:10.645
(male #6)
'It seems she was able
to turn away from the blast.'

1:09:10.647 --> 1:09:12.614
'Most of the burns and glass
were down the right side'

1:09:12.616 --> 1:09:14.249
'of her face and neck.'

1:09:14.251 --> 1:09:15.783
Slight swelling of her brain

1:09:15.785 --> 1:09:17.886
indicates she suffered
a mild concussion.

1:09:20.322 --> 1:09:22.524
'We'd like to keep her here
for the next 48 hours'

1:09:22.526 --> 1:09:25.260
to monitor her progress.

1:09:25.262 --> 1:09:27.061
She's very lucky, Mr. Radden.

1:09:28.664 --> 1:09:30.231
It doesn't feel that way.

1:09:31.934 --> 1:09:33.334
Thank you, doc.

1:09:34.837 --> 1:09:36.571
I'll check on her later.

1:09:54.723 --> 1:09:57.025
- Any news?
- Yeah.

1:09:57.027 --> 1:09:59.527
She's gonna be okay, bro.
She's stable for now.

1:09:59.529 --> 1:10:01.796
Oh, thank God.

1:10:01.798 --> 1:10:04.866
So, how's the shop?

1:10:04.868 --> 1:10:08.503
(Bulger)
'The truck's a big heap
of burnt metal.'

1:10:08.505 --> 1:10:12.040
'So there goes our shot,
the last race of the season.'

1:10:12.042 --> 1:10:13.975
'Jesus, man. I just,
I don't know'

1:10:13.977 --> 1:10:15.877
'who the hell would do
somethin' like this.'

1:10:17.413 --> 1:10:19.214
(Robbie)
'Trent?'

1:10:19.216 --> 1:10:21.216
(Bulger)
'No, man.'

1:10:21.218 --> 1:10:23.051
'Not even Trent would do this.'

1:10:25.521 --> 1:10:27.922
I'm gonna grab some stuff
and head back to the hospital.

1:10:29.725 --> 1:10:31.726
- Rick.
- 'Yeah.'

1:10:33.829 --> 1:10:35.396
I know who did this.

1:10:36.565 --> 1:10:37.832
What?

1:10:39.401 --> 1:10:40.935
Who? Wh-who did this?

1:10:42.705 --> 1:10:44.973
There's a dude
I used to steal cars for.

1:10:47.076 --> 1:10:49.877
He thinks I owe him.

1:10:49.879 --> 1:10:52.347
- This is you?
- I'm sorry.

1:10:52.349 --> 1:10:53.815
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1:10:59.088 --> 1:11:00.655
You brought this into my home?

1:11:02.458 --> 1:11:05.260
What else, Dez? What else
do I got to worry about?

1:11:05.262 --> 1:11:08.596
- Look, I'm gonna handle it.
- Oh, you're gonna handle it?

1:11:08.598 --> 1:11:11.032
I don't even know
what that means.

1:11:11.034 --> 1:11:12.467
I'm sorry.

1:11:12.469 --> 1:11:15.603
My wife is in the hospital
because of you.

1:11:18.374 --> 1:11:21.209
I can't even look at you
right now. Just walk away!

1:11:21.211 --> 1:11:24.545
- Rick, man. Just listen--
- Walk away, kid.

1:11:24.547 --> 1:11:25.980
Walk away.

1:11:35.658 --> 1:11:38.326
[grunting]

1:11:38.328 --> 1:11:40.194
[sobbing]

1:11:42.998 --> 1:11:44.966
[screams]

1:11:57.413 --> 1:11:59.647
I heard you had some
car trouble. Tough break.

1:11:59.649 --> 1:12:02.417
What do I gotta do so I never
have to see your face again?

1:12:02.419 --> 1:12:04.519
Gee, Dez. That's askin' a lot.

1:12:04.521 --> 1:12:07.355
Just tell me what I have to do
and I'll do it.

1:12:10.926 --> 1:12:15.663
Get me another Rolls.
Same color. I like that color.

1:12:15.665 --> 1:12:17.165
Yeah, it's a good color.

1:12:19.802 --> 1:12:21.969
And this one's on the house.

1:12:21.971 --> 1:12:25.373
It's all yours
and then you and I are done.

1:12:25.375 --> 1:12:29.277
Look at you. Those white folks
must be doin' somethin' right.

1:12:42.491 --> 1:12:43.891
Sure about this?

1:12:46.729 --> 1:12:48.062
Okay.

1:12:54.136 --> 1:12:55.636
♪ Panterra

1:12:58.307 --> 1:13:00.908
Come on, man.
Do you know who I am?

1:13:00.910 --> 1:13:03.544
Dude, I should be on this list.

1:13:03.546 --> 1:13:05.913
'Check your list.'

1:13:05.915 --> 1:13:08.149
- Clean 'em nice.
- You too.

1:13:11.086 --> 1:13:12.253
There he is.

1:13:13.756 --> 1:13:16.290
- You got this?
- In my sleep.

1:13:21.163 --> 1:13:23.898
♪ I'mma give it up
if you love me that way ♪

1:13:23.900 --> 1:13:27.335
♪ Back it up
I'm coming your way ♪

1:13:27.337 --> 1:13:28.669
'Oh.'

1:13:28.671 --> 1:13:31.339
[laughs]

1:13:31.341 --> 1:13:32.907
Oh, I'm sorry.

1:13:32.909 --> 1:13:35.543
Let me fix you up.
You're cute.

1:13:35.545 --> 1:13:37.245
♪ Breaking all the rules

1:13:37.247 --> 1:13:39.881
♪ I got that spark
for your lighter ♪

1:13:39.883 --> 1:13:42.016
♪ You know it's coming soon

1:13:42.018 --> 1:13:45.119
♪ So baby make it
worth my while ♪

1:13:45.121 --> 1:13:46.354
♪ Keep it lit all night

1:13:46.356 --> 1:13:47.789
She's all yours.

1:13:51.427 --> 1:13:54.395
- You scare me sometimes.
- Mm-hmm.

1:13:54.397 --> 1:13:57.698
♪ Breaking all the rules
I got that spark ♪

1:13:57.700 --> 1:14:00.101
[engine revving]

1:14:10.212 --> 1:14:12.947
- You're a man of your word.
- Alright.

1:14:12.949 --> 1:14:14.348
We good?

1:14:16.819 --> 1:14:18.519
The only thing is..

1:14:20.255 --> 1:14:22.590
...I still can't figure out
how the cops found out

1:14:22.592 --> 1:14:24.459
'where we were.'

1:14:24.461 --> 1:14:25.893
Look. Serge, man.

1:14:25.895 --> 1:14:29.063
I told you I didn't have
nothin' to do with that.

1:14:29.065 --> 1:14:31.165
And I told you,
you know what's gonna happen

1:14:31.167 --> 1:14:33.100
if you bring the heat.

1:14:33.102 --> 1:14:35.303
[intense music]

1:14:41.076 --> 1:14:43.010
Freeze! LAPD!

1:14:43.012 --> 1:14:44.745
Keep both hands
where I can see them. Fast!

1:14:44.747 --> 1:14:46.914
- Get back here.
- 'Stay where you are.'

1:14:46.916 --> 1:14:49.383
[dramatic music]

1:15:32.961 --> 1:15:34.695
You gonna lecture me?

1:15:34.697 --> 1:15:36.230
(Freeman)
'Would it do any good?'

1:15:39.201 --> 1:15:42.403
An anonymous tip
came in in our system.

1:15:42.405 --> 1:15:44.839
'Told us everything that was
going down here tonight.'

1:15:44.841 --> 1:15:47.842
That sounds like me.

1:15:47.844 --> 1:15:50.745
You coulda got yourself
killed here, kid.

1:15:50.747 --> 1:15:52.580
Not on your watch.

1:16:02.591 --> 1:16:04.058
(Rick)
'Okay, baby.'

1:16:07.763 --> 1:16:09.530
You didn't leave me
for a second?

1:16:09.532 --> 1:16:10.932
No way.

1:16:13.201 --> 1:16:15.202
What did Bulger say
about the truck?

1:16:15.204 --> 1:16:16.837
Ah, don't worry about that.

1:16:18.907 --> 1:16:21.008
I don't know.
Maybe it's time to..

1:16:23.946 --> 1:16:25.980
Maybe it's time to call it.

1:16:57.946 --> 1:17:02.049
(Robbie)
The engine management system,
the fuel delivery, the shocks..

1:17:02.051 --> 1:17:03.718
The entire wiring..

1:17:03.720 --> 1:17:05.519
That's not to mention
the damn engine.

1:17:07.389 --> 1:17:09.890
Man, that's gonna be
150 grand, man, easy.

1:17:12.260 --> 1:17:15.997
Uh, hey, guys.
Check it out.

1:17:20.335 --> 1:17:21.736
Still got this.

1:17:27.275 --> 1:17:29.343
Yo, this is Dez.

1:17:29.345 --> 1:17:30.911
Yeah, I know.

1:17:30.913 --> 1:17:33.814
[clears throat]
You still workin' in the, uh

1:17:33.816 --> 1:17:35.182
in the repair shop, man?

1:17:35.184 --> 1:17:38.419
Yo, Chris man, this is Dez.

1:17:38.421 --> 1:17:41.956
Quick question, are you still
good with a welder?

1:17:41.958 --> 1:17:44.925
Yo, um, this is Dez.

1:17:44.927 --> 1:17:46.927
I kinda need a favor
from you, man.

1:17:55.837 --> 1:17:58.339
Dez gave it to me.

1:17:58.341 --> 1:17:59.874
Tanya made it.

1:18:02.978 --> 1:18:05.179
He's a good kid.

1:18:05.181 --> 1:18:06.580
They both are.

1:18:09.117 --> 1:18:11.218
I really liked having him here
this summer.

1:18:13.288 --> 1:18:16.490
- You know, like a real family.
- Baby.

1:18:16.492 --> 1:18:19.527
Oh, come on,
it wasn't his fault.

1:18:19.529 --> 1:18:21.929
And it wasn't your fault either.

1:18:23.699 --> 1:18:25.299
And you trusted your gut

1:18:25.301 --> 1:18:27.601
and made the right choice
bringin' him here.

1:18:49.424 --> 1:18:51.592
Well, it's about time
you got here.

1:18:51.594 --> 1:18:53.561
Dude, I can't deal
with this shit right now.

1:18:53.563 --> 1:18:56.230
Come on, boss.
Got somethin' to show you.

1:18:56.232 --> 1:18:58.499
Come on, man. Trust me.

1:19:07.776 --> 1:19:08.843
Yeah.

1:19:12.414 --> 1:19:13.914
What's goin' on?

1:19:18.086 --> 1:19:19.687
Freeman?

1:19:19.689 --> 1:19:21.422
Remember the old race truck
you donated

1:19:21.424 --> 1:19:23.858
to Nexgeneracers?

1:19:23.860 --> 1:19:27.261
- Yeah.
- We donated it back to you.

1:19:27.263 --> 1:19:30.364
And the spare engine didn't get
destroyed during the break-in.

1:19:30.366 --> 1:19:32.099
She's still firin', boss.

1:19:36.304 --> 1:19:38.806
It's all great, guys..

1:19:38.808 --> 1:19:41.408
...but the season's over.

1:19:41.410 --> 1:19:43.778
We can still run
in the Challenge Cup.

1:19:43.780 --> 1:19:45.613
'Show those sponsors
what we can do.'

1:19:53.288 --> 1:19:55.589
Can you get it ready
by Saturday?

1:19:55.591 --> 1:19:56.891
Oh, yeah.

1:19:56.893 --> 1:19:58.125
We got a whole crew
of people

1:19:58.127 --> 1:20:00.094
workin' here to make
that happen.

1:20:00.096 --> 1:20:02.329
Let me introduce you.

1:20:02.331 --> 1:20:06.167
'Letty Simons,
Nexgeneracers, 1998.'

1:20:06.169 --> 1:20:09.970
Chris La Rose,
Nexgeneracers, 2006.

1:20:09.972 --> 1:20:12.373
Ron Ricton, 2015.

1:20:13.909 --> 1:20:15.676
And our man here, Dez..

1:20:17.078 --> 1:20:18.646
'...made it all happen.'

1:20:25.187 --> 1:20:26.654
Thanks, kid.

1:20:30.759 --> 1:20:33.127
And the tires look new. Where'd
you guys get all this stuff?

1:20:33.129 --> 1:20:36.997
Oh, man. You know how I roll.

1:20:36.999 --> 1:20:39.233
'I wanna introduce you
to two more people, come on.'

1:20:43.538 --> 1:20:45.806
Rick, this is Bob
and Charlotte Henderson

1:20:45.808 --> 1:20:47.274
from Protect The Harvest.

1:20:47.276 --> 1:20:48.676
- Glad to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

1:20:48.678 --> 1:20:50.177
Hi.

1:20:50.179 --> 1:20:52.313
They're Nexgeneracers'
greatest benefactors.

1:20:52.315 --> 1:20:55.316
They wanna sponsor the team
for the Challenge Cup.

1:20:55.318 --> 1:20:57.051
I hope you like the idea
because this guy's

1:20:57.053 --> 1:20:59.954
already spent about
half the money.

1:20:59.956 --> 1:21:03.490
When Charles Wilson and Rodney
Reid founded Nexgeneracers

1:21:03.492 --> 1:21:06.994
it was their dream to get
one of their kids on the podium.

1:21:06.996 --> 1:21:10.798
Now we can get this car goin',
but Dez won't take the wheel

1:21:10.800 --> 1:21:12.600
unless you're at the helm.

1:21:15.070 --> 1:21:19.707
Mr. and Mrs. Henderson,
you guys got yourselves a team.

1:21:19.709 --> 1:21:22.376
- Thank you very much.
- That's good. Good.

1:21:25.647 --> 1:21:27.815
(Seaver)
'Here we are
in Chandler, Arizona'

1:21:27.817 --> 1:21:30.251
'at the Wild Horse Pass
Motorsports Park'

1:21:30.253 --> 1:21:32.386
'for everyone's favorite
event of the year.'

1:21:32.388 --> 1:21:34.555
- 'The Challenge Cup.'
- 'Throw out the points.'

1:21:34.557 --> 1:21:37.758
(Arnold)
'This is open to all drivers
and the gloves are off.'

1:21:37.760 --> 1:21:41.395
'Everyone's looking
for next year's sponsorship.'

1:21:41.397 --> 1:21:43.764
Actually, Dave, we were excited
about the opportunity

1:21:43.766 --> 1:21:45.232
and idea of coming out
and expanding

1:21:45.234 --> 1:21:47.167
our program
into the off road series.

1:21:47.169 --> 1:21:49.103
I wanna try and do my homework.
I wanna know that we're gonna be

1:21:49.105 --> 1:21:51.572
able to put together a good team
to win 'cause, we hate to lose.

1:22:02.384 --> 1:22:04.418
Alright, team. Ready!

1:22:06.454 --> 1:22:08.122
What? What is it?

1:22:08.124 --> 1:22:10.124
You know, there's a white woman
standin' behind you.

1:22:12.360 --> 1:22:15.195
Honey, what are you doin' here?

1:22:15.197 --> 1:22:17.364
I came to see my family race.

1:22:18.700 --> 1:22:21.035
You better get
that Challenge Cup, kid.

1:22:21.037 --> 1:22:23.470
We're gonna try.

1:22:23.472 --> 1:22:24.805
Try?

1:22:27.042 --> 1:22:29.243
You're Rick Radden.

1:22:29.245 --> 1:22:31.011
You're damn right, I am.

1:22:33.949 --> 1:22:35.482
Get it.

1:22:39.888 --> 1:22:43.390
What are you animals lookin' at?
Get back to work.

1:22:43.392 --> 1:22:46.293
(male announcer)
'Hey, fans, make sure to stop by
at the Team Associated'

1:22:46.295 --> 1:22:48.295
'track cars and racers'

1:22:48.297 --> 1:22:50.965
'still now an off-road truck.'

1:22:50.967 --> 1:22:53.901
'All drivers to pre-grid.
All drivers to pre-grid.'

1:22:53.903 --> 1:22:56.103
'The race is about to start.'

1:22:56.105 --> 1:22:58.072
Hey, kid,
you ever see "Mad Max?"

1:22:58.074 --> 1:23:00.307
Uh.. Yeah, why?

1:23:00.309 --> 1:23:02.743
Bunch of crazy white boys
with big trucks

1:23:02.745 --> 1:23:05.679
not carin' about points
or damage.

1:23:05.681 --> 1:23:08.415
It's gonna be kinda like that.
So be ready.

1:23:11.252 --> 1:23:13.320
Thanks for the heads up.

1:23:13.322 --> 1:23:14.488
I think.

1:23:14.490 --> 1:23:16.924
Just for the record

1:23:16.926 --> 1:23:19.093
you win or lose

1:23:19.095 --> 1:23:20.995
I'm proud to have you
as part of my team.

1:23:22.364 --> 1:23:24.098
Thanks, Rick.

1:23:24.100 --> 1:23:26.567
[instrumental music]

1:23:29.871 --> 1:23:32.840
(Seaver)
'Team Radden is back
after not finishing the season'

1:23:32.842 --> 1:23:36.477
'with a new truck Number 21
and a new sponsor.'

1:23:36.479 --> 1:23:39.713
(Arnold)
'Protect the Harvest is a
non-profit supporting ranchers'

1:23:39.715 --> 1:23:43.217
'farmers and underdogs
and they picked the right team.'

1:23:43.219 --> 1:23:45.319
(Seaver)
'Well, they're gonna be up
against their old driver'

1:23:45.321 --> 1:23:48.689
'Trent Lerion whose got himself
a new ride in the Toyota.'

1:23:48.691 --> 1:23:50.591
(Arnold)
'This should be interesting.'

1:24:06.574 --> 1:24:08.242
(Seaver)
'Let's take a look at the grid''

1:24:08.244 --> 1:24:10.010
'We'll go right into
the front row inside.'

1:24:10.012 --> 1:24:11.545
'It starts
on the pole position'

1:24:11.547 --> 1:24:13.714
'and drives that black and green
Monster energy'

1:24:13.716 --> 1:24:16.683
'Number 99, it's Kyle LeDuc.'

1:24:16.685 --> 1:24:19.319
'On the outside
in that Red Bull BFGoodrich'

1:24:19.321 --> 1:24:21.889
'Number 7, it's Riez Enzie.'

1:24:21.891 --> 1:24:25.559
(Arnold)
'Back in row two, that familiar
red, white and blue Number 17'

1:24:25.561 --> 1:24:28.729
'he's backed by Lucas oil
and Goodrich Tires'

1:24:28.731 --> 1:24:30.531
'Carl Renezeder.'

1:24:30.533 --> 1:24:33.534
'And on the outside,
that black and yellow Number 21'

1:24:33.536 --> 1:24:35.169
'backed by Protect The Harvest'

1:24:35.171 --> 1:24:37.571
'and Rockstar energy
is Dez Truss.'

1:24:37.573 --> 1:24:40.007
(Seaver)
'On his tail in row three
is Number 32'

1:24:40.009 --> 1:24:43.744
'Trent Lerion qualify just two
tenths behind Dez Truss.'

1:24:43.746 --> 1:24:46.547
'I hope Protect The Harvest
can protect his backside.'

1:24:46.549 --> 1:24:48.882
'Up on the inside
in row three..'

1:24:48.884 --> 1:24:52.019
Renezeder's top dog.
I wouldn't worry about Trent.

1:24:52.021 --> 1:24:54.021
Trent? Who's Trent?

1:24:54.023 --> 1:24:56.023
[chuckles]
That's the spirit, kid.

1:24:56.025 --> 1:24:58.025
(Trent)
'Okay, here we go, T-bone.'

1:24:58.027 --> 1:24:59.893
'Let's kick some ass, Harv.'

1:24:59.895 --> 1:25:02.129
(Seaver)
'We are ready to go green
on this year's'

1:25:02.131 --> 1:25:04.865
'Pro 4 Challenge Cup
at Wild Horse Pass.'

1:25:04.867 --> 1:25:07.434
Just another day at the track.

1:25:07.436 --> 1:25:09.603
(male announcer)
'And we are green,
green, green.'

1:25:09.605 --> 1:25:11.805
[crowd cheering]

1:25:13.908 --> 1:25:16.376
[intense music]

1:25:22.617 --> 1:25:24.718
Rick, you weren't playin'
about that "Mad Max," man.

1:25:24.720 --> 1:25:26.453
Welcome to Thunderdome.

1:25:27.956 --> 1:25:29.456
White people.

1:25:42.904 --> 1:25:44.938
I'm gonna..

1:25:44.940 --> 1:25:47.407
(Seaver)
'Oh, it's just..
It's the K rail in Turn 3.'

1:25:47.409 --> 1:25:49.309
You're over-rotating.

1:25:49.311 --> 1:25:51.078
(Arnold)
'And now, it looked
half important.'

1:25:51.080 --> 1:25:53.013
Oh, man.

1:25:53.015 --> 1:25:55.582
Come on, baby.

1:25:55.584 --> 1:25:57.684
(Rick)
'Dez, it's gettin'
a little hairy ahead.'

1:25:57.686 --> 1:25:59.353
Tempers are flarin'.

1:25:59.355 --> 1:26:01.522
'Hang back and let 'em
bang it out for a bit.'

1:26:15.203 --> 1:26:16.803
(Seaver)
'Now we've got
our first tangle.'

1:26:16.805 --> 1:26:18.472
'Fifty-one might drive
away from this'

1:26:18.474 --> 1:26:20.507
'but 74 is done for the day.'

1:26:20.509 --> 1:26:22.676
(Arnold)
'These guys are battlin' hard
out here.'

1:26:22.678 --> 1:26:25.345
'Fighting tooth and nail,
it's dirty out here.'

1:26:25.347 --> 1:26:29.049
'Oh! And the Number 2 McGrath
lands on Renezeder's sunroof.'

1:26:29.051 --> 1:26:31.685
'McGrath is done for the day.'

1:26:31.687 --> 1:26:33.887
(Seaver)
'And that is gonna bring out
a caution.'

1:26:33.889 --> 1:26:36.523
(Arnold)
'We'll clear the victims
and then bunch all these trucks'

1:26:36.525 --> 1:26:39.493
'back up behind the base car
to restart in formation.'

1:26:39.495 --> 1:26:42.829
(Seaver)
'Wow, only five laps in
and already two trucks out.'

1:26:42.831 --> 1:26:44.731
'Heck of a start
to this one, folks.'

1:26:48.503 --> 1:26:50.504
(male announcer)
'Green flag is up.

1:26:50.506 --> 1:26:53.507
'And we are green,
green, green.'

1:26:53.509 --> 1:26:55.576
(Seaver)
'Kyle LeDuc, Bryce Menzies,
Carl Renezeder'

1:26:55.578 --> 1:26:58.345
'Trent Lerion, Greg Adler
in the Number 10 car comin'.'

1:26:58.347 --> 1:27:00.047
'Lerion and him
are side by side.'

1:27:00.049 --> 1:27:02.149
'But it's gonna be Kyle LeDuc
up the hill first.'

1:27:02.151 --> 1:27:04.084
(Arnold)
'Bryce is gonna try to close
that back up.'

1:27:04.086 --> 1:27:06.887
'LeDuc skies it out
over the ski-jump'

1:27:06.889 --> 1:27:09.056
'and then charges hard
into Turn 3.'

1:27:09.058 --> 1:27:11.158
'The dangerous and read about
right-hander.'

1:27:15.997 --> 1:27:19.933
(Rick)
'Okay, kid. Get past Trent and
then let's make some moves.'

1:27:19.935 --> 1:27:21.668
Get this next corner high.

1:27:23.171 --> 1:27:25.372
'That's it, that's it.

1:27:25.374 --> 1:27:28.075
Alright, you might have to worry
about Trent a little bit.

1:27:28.077 --> 1:27:31.378
(Seaver)
'It's our newest and youngest
Pro 4 driver Dez Truss'

1:27:31.380 --> 1:27:33.380
'tryin' to make some noise
in the 21 truck'

1:27:33.382 --> 1:27:35.616
'taking on its former driver,
Trent Lerion.'

1:27:35.618 --> 1:27:38.585
He might be in a better truck,
but you're a better driver.'

1:27:44.058 --> 1:27:46.226
(Arnold)
'Now they're side by side
in the whoop section.'

1:27:46.228 --> 1:27:48.028
Throttle it.

1:27:48.030 --> 1:27:49.796
(Arnold)
...'Dez Truss is gonna slide
underneath.'

1:27:49.798 --> 1:27:52.532
'He's got Lerion
in his rearview mirror.'

1:27:52.534 --> 1:27:53.834
No, no, no, no, no!

1:27:59.407 --> 1:28:00.574
(Seaver)
'Oh, and look at this battle
goin' on'

1:28:00.576 --> 1:28:02.075
'in the front of the pack.'

1:28:02.077 --> 1:28:03.644
'Bryce Menzies got tired
of followin'.'

1:28:03.646 --> 1:28:05.112
'Now he said
it's my time to lead'

1:28:05.114 --> 1:28:07.214
'lookin' to make a move
on the inside.'

1:28:07.216 --> 1:28:09.383
(Arnold)
'Coming out of Turn 4,
it's gonna be a drag race'

1:28:09.385 --> 1:28:11.184
'down the front straightaway.'

1:28:13.888 --> 1:28:16.290
- 'Oh!'
- 'LeDuc and Menzies crashed.'

1:28:19.761 --> 1:28:22.462
(Arnold)
'So that's it for last year's
champ Kyle LeDuc.'

1:28:22.464 --> 1:28:25.899
(Seaver)
'He's out of the truck, which is
still smoking. That was a big..'

1:28:25.901 --> 1:28:27.901
(Arnold)
'You see, they're also towing
off Bryce Menzies.'

1:28:27.903 --> 1:28:30.504
'We told you the gloves were
gonna come off in this race.'

1:28:30.506 --> 1:28:32.472
'And it has not disappointed.'

1:28:35.143 --> 1:28:38.912
Alright, Dez. Adler's up next.
Stay on target.

1:28:38.914 --> 1:28:41.615
(Arnold)
'With Menzies officially out,
guess who inherits the lead.'

1:28:41.617 --> 1:28:44.418
(Seaver)
'Yeah, it's nine times champ
Carl Renezeder, of course.'

1:28:44.420 --> 1:28:46.920
'Adler moves into second
and a rookie Dez Truss'

1:28:46.922 --> 1:28:49.022
'is in a podium position.'

1:28:49.024 --> 1:28:52.659
Head down, mouth shut.
Get ready to roll.

1:28:52.661 --> 1:28:54.661
(male announcer)
'And we are
green, green, green.'

1:28:56.931 --> 1:28:59.466
(Seaver)
'Carl Renezeder is gonna lead
them into Turn 1'

1:28:59.468 --> 1:29:02.669
'followed by Adler, Truss,
Trent Lerion and Doug Matag'

1:29:02.671 --> 1:29:04.971
'and that is it.
Five trucks left.'

1:29:04.973 --> 1:29:06.840
(Arnold)
'Attrition is the name
of the game here'

1:29:06.842 --> 1:29:08.008
'in today's Challenge Cup.'

1:29:08.010 --> 1:29:09.276
'At least this will cut down'

1:29:09.278 --> 1:29:10.877
'on the collisions.'

1:29:10.879 --> 1:29:12.779
- 'Oh! Whoa!'
- Oh!'

1:29:15.883 --> 1:29:18.885
(Seaver)
'And Adler goes over the gear
rail and sticks the landing.'

1:29:18.887 --> 1:29:20.287
(Arnold)
'I give it a ten.'

1:29:20.289 --> 1:29:22.889
I guess Adler's done.

1:29:22.891 --> 1:29:25.559
(Arnold)
'Those deep ruts in Turn 3
make it a dangerous corner'

1:29:25.561 --> 1:29:27.894
'especially when tryin'
to pass.'

1:29:27.896 --> 1:29:30.230
(Seaver)
'And now we are down
to just four trucks.'

1:29:31.799 --> 1:29:33.800
It's me and you, Carl.

1:29:33.802 --> 1:29:35.736
Me and you.

1:29:35.738 --> 1:29:37.704
(male announcer)
'We are gonna go ahead
and let the track'

1:29:37.706 --> 1:29:40.874
'go green, green, green.'

1:29:40.876 --> 1:29:43.310
(Seaver)
'Renezeder, Truss,
Lerion and Matag.'

1:29:43.312 --> 1:29:45.812
'I can tell ya, one of these
guys won't make the podium.'

1:29:45.814 --> 1:29:47.714
'That is a safe bet.'

1:29:55.656 --> 1:29:57.124
Stay on him, stay on him.

1:30:00.094 --> 1:30:02.262
(Seaver)
'Though a lot of people
doubted Rick Radden'

1:30:02.264 --> 1:30:04.197
'when he let Lerion go
this season--'

1:30:04.199 --> 1:30:06.533
(Arnold)
'Here comes Lerion
to try to prove it'

1:30:06.535 --> 1:30:09.336
'but Truss is having
none of it.'

1:30:09.338 --> 1:30:10.737
(Rick)
'Listen, now take him.'

1:30:10.739 --> 1:30:12.672
You look clear on the next one.

1:30:12.674 --> 1:30:14.174
Take a shot. Go in hard.

1:30:16.711 --> 1:30:19.880
(Arnold)
'I'll tell ya, when Carl
Renezeder is driving this well'

1:30:19.882 --> 1:30:22.115
'it's very tough for anyone
to get around him.'

1:30:22.117 --> 1:30:24.151
'Let alone
a 17-year-old rookie.'

1:30:26.254 --> 1:30:29.089
(Seaver)
'Yet here comes Truss tryin'
to slide underneath Renezeder.'

1:30:29.091 --> 1:30:31.958
'I don't think there's enough
room.. Oh, contact.'

1:30:31.960 --> 1:30:33.960
(Seaver)
'Renezeder's okay.
Truss gets turned around.'

1:30:33.962 --> 1:30:37.531
- 'And Lerion flies by.'
-  <i>Adios, succos!</i>

1:30:37.533 --> 1:30:38.865
Dude!

1:30:38.867 --> 1:30:41.268
[engine cranking]

1:30:41.270 --> 1:30:43.703
(Seaver)
'Oh, if Truss can't get
that truck refired'

1:30:43.705 --> 1:30:45.772
'that'll be it for Team Radden''

1:30:45.774 --> 1:30:48.074
Excellent! Excellent!
He's all yours.

1:30:48.076 --> 1:30:50.110
(Seaver)
'And the rest of the field
continues on.'

1:30:51.813 --> 1:30:53.013
Come on.

1:30:54.382 --> 1:30:57.217
It ain't startin'. Come on!

1:30:57.219 --> 1:30:58.819
(Seaver)
'Oh, we've come to a caution.'

1:30:58.821 --> 1:31:00.954
'That will buy Truss
a few more seconds'

1:31:00.956 --> 1:31:03.223
'to try to get
that truck restarted.'

1:31:03.225 --> 1:31:05.158
(Robbie)
'Dez, listen,
it might just be flooded'

1:31:05.160 --> 1:31:07.127
'so turn off the fuel pump
and crank it a couple times.'

1:31:07.129 --> 1:31:09.596
(Dez)
'Okay, okay, I'm tryin' it now.'

1:31:09.598 --> 1:31:10.997
Come on!

1:31:13.134 --> 1:31:14.501
[engine revving]

1:31:14.503 --> 1:31:16.503
- God!
- 'Wait now.'

1:31:16.505 --> 1:31:19.105
(Seaver)
'Truss is not out yet.
He's got that truck restarted'

1:31:19.107 --> 1:31:20.674
'and comin' out
of the yellow flag'

1:31:20.676 --> 1:31:22.642
'will bunch these trucks
right back up.'

1:31:22.644 --> 1:31:23.977
(Arnold)
'Well, the good news is,
this is gonna'

1:31:23.979 --> 1:31:25.812
'put him back in that pack.'

1:31:25.814 --> 1:31:29.015
'But the bad news is,
he's lost his podium position'

1:31:29.017 --> 1:31:31.084
'and he doesn't have much time
to work with.'

1:31:34.422 --> 1:31:36.456
(Rick)
'Get back in there.
We're not out of this.'

1:31:36.458 --> 1:31:39.659
We got three cars to beat,
three laps to do it.

1:31:39.661 --> 1:31:42.128
- 'Make it happen, kid.'
- Check!

1:31:42.130 --> 1:31:44.664
(male announcer)
'Race band 17 of Renezeder
will start the race.'

1:31:44.666 --> 1:31:45.999
'Here we go.'

1:31:46.001 --> 1:31:48.034
'And we are
green, green, green.'

1:31:55.776 --> 1:31:59.279
(Seaver)
'Trent Lerion's on Renezeder's
bumper looking for an opening.'

1:32:01.883 --> 1:32:03.884
(Arnold)
'Oh, but here comes Dez Truss'

1:32:03.886 --> 1:32:06.553
'trying to claim a podium slot
back from the pack.'

1:32:06.555 --> 1:32:10.123
(Seaver)
'He dives under the 81 and he's
gonna slack right into third.'

1:32:10.125 --> 1:32:11.358
Awesome.

1:32:24.639 --> 1:32:26.973
(Arnold)
'Lerion now holding on
to second place.'

1:32:26.975 --> 1:32:28.875
'Dez Truss is on the move
giving Lerion'

1:32:28.877 --> 1:32:30.810
'a little love tap
to come out of the corner.'

1:32:30.812 --> 1:32:33.246
(Seaver)
'They are door to door
over the whoop section.'

1:32:33.248 --> 1:32:36.383
'Truss slides in underneath
and he goes up on two wheels'

1:32:36.385 --> 1:32:38.351
'as he passes Lerion
into second'

1:32:38.353 --> 1:32:39.719
'and the white flag is out.'

1:32:41.355 --> 1:32:42.923
Son of a bitch!

1:32:42.925 --> 1:32:44.658
(Seaver)
'Renezeder's still in the lead'

1:32:44.660 --> 1:32:47.527
'in the final lap.'

1:32:47.529 --> 1:32:49.062
(Arnold)
'He's comin' up
with that left-hander again.'

1:32:49.064 --> 1:32:50.564
'If he's gonna make
something happen'

1:32:50.566 --> 1:32:52.766
'this corner's gonna be
his best opportunity.'

1:32:52.768 --> 1:32:54.768
'He wasn't so successful
last time.'

1:32:54.770 --> 1:32:57.370
- I'm going for it.
- 'No, no, no. Hold on.'

1:32:57.372 --> 1:32:58.672
- What?
- 'It's an obvious move.'

1:32:58.674 --> 1:33:01.341
(Rick)
'He'd expect you
to turn to him.'

1:33:01.343 --> 1:33:03.443
(Seaver)
'Oh, Truss missed
his chance there.'

1:33:03.445 --> 1:33:05.779
'I don't see him
catching Renezeder now.'

1:33:05.781 --> 1:33:08.214
But you bet he won't expect it
in Turn 3.

1:33:08.216 --> 1:33:09.482
Got it.

1:33:12.553 --> 1:33:13.787
He's yours, Dez.

1:33:17.391 --> 1:33:19.593
(Seaver)
'Oh, Truss passes Renezeder
in Turn 3.'

1:33:19.595 --> 1:33:21.561
Yes, go.

1:33:21.563 --> 1:33:23.463
(Seaver)
'And he's pullin' away
with one turn to go.'

1:33:23.465 --> 1:33:25.932
'What a run to the finish.
Dez Truss goes for the match.'

1:33:25.934 --> 1:33:28.435
'To the front, to the back,
to the front!'

1:33:28.437 --> 1:33:29.636
Come on, Dez.

1:33:42.717 --> 1:33:44.451
[cheering]

1:33:44.453 --> 1:33:47.554
- You did it, kid!
- Ha ha!

1:33:47.556 --> 1:33:50.824
(Seaver)
'And Dez Truss wins
the Challenge Cup.'

1:33:50.826 --> 1:33:54.728
'Ladies and gentleman, that was
one of the craziest races'

1:33:54.730 --> 1:33:56.129
'I have ever seen.'

1:33:59.567 --> 1:34:01.568
Get me Forrest Lucas.

1:34:01.570 --> 1:34:03.803
I've got a team
for him to sponsor.

1:34:05.740 --> 1:34:08.208
[instrumental music]

1:34:11.345 --> 1:34:13.847
[indistinct chatter]

1:34:27.194 --> 1:34:28.928
<i>(Rick)</i>
<i>Americans love to race.</i>

1:34:28.930 --> 1:34:30.664
<i>We love winners.</i>

1:34:30.666 --> 1:34:34.000
<i>We love a good underdog story.</i>

1:34:34.002 --> 1:34:36.469
<i>And we love knowing</i>
<i>that anyone</i>

1:34:36.471 --> 1:34:38.772
<i>no matter who,</i>
<i>no matter where they come from</i>

1:34:38.774 --> 1:34:41.574
<i>has a chance to stand</i>
<i>on the top of that box.</i>

1:34:47.615 --> 1:34:49.816
<i>But being the fastest</i>

1:34:49.818 --> 1:34:54.120
<i>means that someone else</i>
<i>always wants to take you down.</i>

1:34:54.122 --> 1:34:56.589
[intense music]

1:35:07.168 --> 1:35:09.302
We're locked down here.

1:35:09.304 --> 1:35:11.204
How's the perimeter?

1:35:11.206 --> 1:35:13.773
(male #7)
'We're good, boss.
No one's comin' in or out.'

1:35:19.346 --> 1:35:22.215
Makin' a big mistake, son.

1:35:22.217 --> 1:35:24.517
I got this.

1:35:24.519 --> 1:35:26.252
[crowd cheering]

1:35:27.655 --> 1:35:29.322
(Glenda)
'Hey, Dez!'

1:35:29.324 --> 1:35:30.890
Kick his butt!

1:35:32.827 --> 1:35:35.895
I-isn't anyone cheerin' for me?

1:35:35.897 --> 1:35:38.865
- I got 20 bucks on you.
- 'Go, Dez!'

1:35:38.867 --> 1:35:40.433
You ready, kid?

1:35:40.435 --> 1:35:42.535
[engine revving]

1:35:42.537 --> 1:35:45.004
[intense music]

1:36:00.855 --> 1:36:03.323
[instrumental music]

1:37:51.498 --> 1:37:53.967
[instrumental music]
